kimi","native":"月見るな"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/360414"},"role":"MAIN"}]},"description":"Eeyuu, a high school boy, has a problem! Two childhood friends \"Shio\" and \"Akari\" who go to the same high school are too cute! If they find out that I'm the only one looking sexually at them now that they've grown up, even though I have no intention of doing so... that would be too much! On the other hand, the two childhood friends also have their own secrets...? It's so awkward! It's complicated! But childhood friends are the best! A sweet and impatient love triangle love comedy where you can't be honest!\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Kodansha, translated)","duration":24,"endDate":{"day":24,"month":3,"year":2026},"genres":["Comedy","Romance"],"id":189565,"meanScore":62,"popularity":15066,"rankings":[{"allTime":false,"context":"highest rated","format":"TV","rank":35,"type":"RATED","year":2026},{"allTime":false,"context":"most popular","format":"TV","rank":46,"type":"POPULAR","year":2026},{"allTime":false,"context":"most popular","format":"TV","rank":27,"season":"WINTER","type":"POPULAR","year":2026}],"recommendations":{"edges":[{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/126192-BQvOYqBnotKx.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#e45d93","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx126192-3fFbZJFSwrHH.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx126192-3fFbZJFSwrHH.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx126192-3fFbZJFSwrHH.jpg"},"description":"The protagonist, Naoya, is a first-year in high school. He asks out Saki, a girl he has been in love with, and she agrees to be his girlfriend. He's currently on cloud nine. But then, a beautiful girl named Nagisa comes up to Naoya one day and tells him that she wants to go out with him. Naoya feels himself wavering because Nagisa is such a good girl, and he comes to a decision! A new kind of romcom from a rather unexpected decision is about to begin!\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Crunchyroll)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":126192,"idMal":43969,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":63,"season":"SUMMER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/126192","startDate":{"day":3,"month":7,"year":2021},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Girlfriend, Girlfriend","native":"カノジョも彼女","romaji":"Kanojo mo Kanojo","userPreferred":"Kanojo mo Kanojo"},"trailer":{"id":"NDHyMF_jgTQ","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/NDHyMF_jgTQ/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/171457-VBH6gmvCKHwV.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#0d6be4","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx171457-nmMIk0gNiWsm.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx171457-nmMIk0gNiWsm.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx171457-nmMIk0gNiWsm.jpg"},"description":"Kazuhiko Nukumizu is a high school boy content to blend in with the background mob, until he witnessed his more popular classmate Anna Yanami get dumped by her childhood friend. He felt like he had to try to comfort Yanami, but this led him to become entangled with other girls who have met defeat at love?","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":171457,"idMal":57524,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":81,"season":"SUMMER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/171457","startDate":{"day":14,"month":7,"year":2024},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Makeine: Too Many Losing Heroines!","native":"負けヒロインが多すぎる！","romaji":"Make Heroine ga Oosugiru!","userPreferred":"Make Heroine ga Oosugiru!"},"trailer":{"id":"uytJ6_KTCZI","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/uytJ6_KTCZI/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/177552-iLWNEFS7t8HM.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#e4a186","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx177552-7XiOf3dGXmNs.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx177552-7XiOf3dGXmNs.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx177552-7XiOf3dGXmNs.jpg"},"description":"Gorgeous from head to toe! The perfect figure! To Kawai Mona, winning hearts comes as naturally as breathing... but the arrival of Kuroiwa Medaka, a new transfer student who won't even give her a second look, turns her school life upside-down! She's lived her whole life being fawned over, so why is he any different? Mona tries everything she can think of to win Medaka over, even getting a bit extreme at times! This new rom-com starring a queen bee and a celibate boy is about to burst onto the scene!\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Crunchyroll)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":177552,"idMal":58853,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":64,"season":"WINTER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/177552","startDate":{"day":7,"month":1,"year":2025},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Medaka Kuroiwa is Impervious to My Charms","native":"黒岩メダカに私の可愛いが通じない","romaji":"Kuroiwa Medaka ni Watashi no Kawaii ga Tsuujinai","userPreferred":"Kuroiwa Medaka ni Watashi no Kawaii ga Tsuujinai"},"trailer":{"id":"pl8FYawHdh0","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pl8FYawHdh0/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/169420-jdvNFYe9Oa4v.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#c9e493","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx169420-u4wDhHlTfX9P.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx169420-u4wDhHlTfX9P.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx169420-u4wDhHlTfX9P.jpg"},"description":"Naoto Watari lives solely for his little sister, Suzushiro, until his chaotic childhood friend, Satsuki, storms back into his life. Without uttering a single word, her very presence ignites buried memories and unravels his rigid routine. As tensions rise and secrets surface, Naoto’s devotion to Suzushiro clashes with unresolved pain, threatening to collapse his fragile world.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Crunchyroll)","episodes":26,"format":"TV","id":169420,"idMal":56693,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":64,"season":"SUMMER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/169420","startDate":{"day":5,"month":7,"year":2025},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Watari-kun's ****** Is about to Collapse","native":"渡くんの××が崩壊寸前","romaji":"Watari-kun no xx ga Houkai Sunzen","userPreferred":"Watari-kun no xx ga Houkai Sunzen"},"trailer":{"id":"d9GC8-kCA_4","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/d9GC8-kCA_4/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/153554-tB8pqiRhaKsy.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#d6861a","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx153554-hHYe9aV6Gvlv.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx153554-hHYe9aV6Gvlv.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx153554-hHYe9aV6Gvlv.jpg"},"description":"Childhood BFFs Himari and Yuu’s vow of friendship hits turbulence when Yuu reunites with his first crush in high school. Himari, who’s never known the fuzzy warmth of a crush, now must confront her feelings. Their shared dreams and peaceful days as a twosome gardening club are tested in this tale of love, flowers, and growing pains!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Crunchyroll, edited)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":153554,"idMal":52709,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":65,"season":"SPRING","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/153554","startDate":{"day":4,"month":4,"year":2025},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Can a Boy-Girl Friendship Survive?","native":"男女の友情は成立する？（いや、 しないっ!!）","romaji":"Danjo no Yuujou wa Seiritsu suru? (Iya, Shinai!!)","userPreferred":"Danjo no Yuujou wa Seiritsu suru? (Iya, Shinai!!)"},"trailer":{"id":"fZH5jDK5qV8","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/fZH5jDK5qV8/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/124675-zPcpWLkxjcSE.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#4386e4","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx124675-fNI06ipb65vy.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx124675-fNI06ipb65vy.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx124675-fNI06ipb65vy.jpg"},"description":"She smiles just for me. Her name is Kachi Shirokusa and she's even an award-winning high school girl writer! And she's beautiful! I know that she's totally out of reach for me, a normal high school kid named Maru Sueharu! But I think something's there... No, there's definitely something there! Or so I thought... but Kachi has a boyfriend?! Seeing me depressed, my friend ever since we were little who's cute, cheerful, and loves to look after others, Shida Kuroha... who also apparently had no problem telling me that she likes me for some reason just suggested, \"Let's get revenge.\"\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Crunchyroll)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":124675,"idMal":43007,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":58,"season":"SPRING","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/124675","startDate":{"day":14,"month":4,"year":2021},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Osamake: Romcom Where The Childhood Friend Won't Lose","native":"幼なじみが絶対に負けないラブコメ","romaji":"Osananajimi ga Zettai ni Makenai Love Come","userPreferred":"Osananajimi ga Zettai ni Makenai Love Come"},"trailer":{"id":"gsTERSk_BZo","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/gsTERSk_BZo/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/162694-PzaToQuFdpsr.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#28aee4","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx162694-QFBei5pbjSh8.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx162694-QFBei5pbjSh8.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx162694-QFBei5pbjSh8.png"},"description":"Rentarou Aijou was rejected 100 times in middle school. He visits a shrine and prays for better luck in high school. The God of Love appears and promises that he’ll soon meet 100 people he’s destined to date. But there’s a catch—once destiny introduces someone to him, the two must happily love each other. If they don’t, they’ll die. What will befall Rentarou and his 100 girlfriends in high school?\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Crunchyroll) ","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":162694,"idMal":54714,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":76,"season":"FALL","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/162694","startDate":{"day":8,"month":10,"year":2023},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"The 100 Girlfriends Who Really, Really, Really, Really, REALLY Love You","native":"君のことが大大大大大好きな100人の彼女","romaji":"Kimi no Koto ga Dai Dai Dai Dai Daisuki na 100-nin no Kanojo","userPreferred":"Kimi no Koto ga Dai Dai Dai Dai Daisuki na 100-nin no Kanojo"},"trailer":{"id":"ls2VNcSifi4","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ls2VNcSifi4/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"coverImage":{"color":"#f1ae5d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx187942-c2cZvunJGfiE.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx187942-c2cZvunJGfiE.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx187942-c2cZvunJGfiE.jpg"},"description":"When Arisu Yamabuki was all alone in bed at night, he was able to find solace in the voice of a radio host who went by “Apollo.” However, one day, she simply stopped broadcasting without any explanation. Years then passed, and Arisu is now a second-year high-schooler. He makes it his mission to search for Apollo, as there is something he wants to tell her. He doesn’t know what she looks like, or even what her real name is, but he manages to get some leads on her in his school’s broadcasting club. That’s where he meets four girls who all dream to get a job where they can make full use of their voices! Just who is Apollo, and how will those four’s dreams pan out?\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: K Manga)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":187942,"idMal":61211,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":70,"season":"WINTER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/187942","startDate":{"day":6,"month":1,"year":2026},"status":"RELEASING","title":{"english":"Tune In to the Midnight Heart","native":"真夜中ハートチューン","romaji":"Mayonaka Heart Tune","userPreferred":"Mayonaka Heart Tune"},"trailer":{"id":"poUibdNvxPQ","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/poUibdNvxPQ/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}}]},"relations":{"edges":[{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/146858-xC0LtJOMulVS.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#50aee4","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx146858-lGlRWfAxqUnL.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx146858-lGlRWfAxqUnL.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/small/bx146858-lGlRWfAxqUnL.jpg"},"description":"Eeyuu, a high school boy, has a problem! Two childhood friends \"Shio\" and \"Akari\" who go to the same high school are too cute! If they find out that I'm the only one looking sexually at them now that they've grown up, even though I have no intention of doing so... that would be too much! On the other hand, the two childhood friends also have their own secrets...? It's so awkward! It's complicated! But childhood friends are the best! A sweet and impatient love triangle love comedy where you can't be honest!\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Kodansha, translated)","endDate":{},"format":"MANGA","genres":["Comedy","Romance"],"id":146858,"idMal":145320,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":69,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/manga/146858","startDate":{"day":22,"month":3,"year":2022},"status":"RELEASING","synonyms":["No more love with the girls","Osananajimi to wa Love Comedy ni Naranai","幼ラブ","OsaLove","소꿉친구와는 러브 코미디를 할 수 없어"],"title":{"english":"You Can’t Be In a Rom-Com with Your Childhood Friends!","native":"幼馴染とはラブコメにならない","romaji":"Osananajimi to wa Love Come ni Naranai","userPreferred":"Osananajimi to wa Love Come ni Naranai"},"trailer":{"id":"4DENC4gw3I0","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/4DENC4gw3I0/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"MANGA"},"relationType":"SOURCE"}]},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/189565","staff":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":129929,"name":{"full":"Shinya Misu"}},"role":"Original Creator"},{"node":{"id":123001,"name":{"full":"Satoshi Kuwabara"}},"role":"Director "},{"node":{"id":110939,"name":{"full":"Mitsutaka Hirota"}},"role":"Series Composition"},{"node":{"id":238966,"name":{"full":"Reina Iwasaki"}},"role":"Character Design"},{"node":{"id":155551,"name":{"full":"Masami Saitou"}},"role":"Art Director"},{"node":{"id":157171,"name":{"full":"Yumi Aburaya"}},"role":"Color Design"},{"node":{"id":147033,"name":{"full":"Shunya Kimura"}},"role":"Director of Photography"},{"node":{"id":157170,"name":{"full":"Wataru Uchida"}},"role":"Editing"},{"node":{"id":101549,"name":{"full":"Satoshi Motoyama"}},"role":"Sound Director"},{"node":{"id":110939,"name":{"full":"Mitsutaka Hirota"}},"role":"Script"},{"node":{"id":123000,"name":{"full":"Mayumi Morita"}},"role":"Script"},{"node":{"id":199405,"name":{"full":"Hikari Kodama"}},"role":"Theme Song Performance (ED)"},{"node":{"id":245301,"name":{"full":"Rin Kusumi"}},"role":"Theme Song Performance (OP)"},{"node":{"id":146863,"name":{"full":"HoneyWorks"}},"role":"Theme Song Performance (OP)"},{"node":{"id":116515,"name":{"full":"Yuu Serizawa"}},"role":"Theme Song Performance (OP)"},{"node":{"id":294238,"name":{"full":"Sae Hiratsuka"}},"role":"Theme Song Performance (OP)"},{"node":{"id":298382,"name":{"full":"Yuuki Yamamoto"}},"role":"Theme Song Performance (OP)"},{"node":{"id":262663,"name":{"full":"Jason Lord"}},"role":"ADR Director (English)"},{"node":{"id":361019,"name":{"full":"Christian Thorsen"}},"role":"ADR Script (English)"},{"node":{"id":254609,"name":{"full":"Susie Nixon"}},"role":"ADR Producer (English)"},{"node":{"id":289903,"name":{"full":"Tina Son"}},"role":"ADR Engineer (English)"}]},"startDate":{"day":6,"month":1,"year":2026},"studios":{"nodes":[{"id":200,"name":"Tezuka Productions"}]},"trailer":{"id":"iSRJs8e5aRo","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/iSRJs8e5aRo/hqdefault.jpg"}}},"updated_at":"2026-03-10T19:51:17.130325+03:00"},"192867":{"value":{"Media":{"averageScore":62,"characters":{"edges":[{"id":531160,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"The android that Akane purchased while she was drunk. She has a gentle and naïve personality.","gender":"Female","id":306706,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b306706-RjG3ZVVDHJ7z.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Nadeshiko","native":"撫子"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/306706"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":531161,"node":{"age":"28","dateOfBirth":{},"description":"An office lady with a friendly and diligent personality. She works for a robotics manufacturer and is a member of the planning team for household robots. ","gender":"Female","id":306668,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b306668-eOaSPL2th3bp.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Akane Tsuda","native":"津田あかね"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/306668"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":546108,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"Akane's kouhai who works in the product planning department of a major electronics manufacturer. Ever since she helped fix her mistakes at work, she has had a crush on Akane.","gender":"Female","id":377554,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b377554-HhPVbzeyqPKU.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Itou-san","native":"伊藤さん"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/377554"},"role":"SUPPORTING"}]},"description":"Office Lady Tsuda Akane, age 28, seems like she’s got it all together. Beautiful, brainy, and an indispensable office worker for a robotics manufacturer, Akane’s admired at work…because her colleagues can’t see her at home. Privately, Akane’s a hot mess with an apartment that looks more like a landfill than a living space. Good thing she drunkenly ordered a new android named Nadeshiko to help her clean up! Well, maybe not good, because the beautiful lady android that arrives is a horny hottie. Akane’s about to get more service than she expected!\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)","duration":5,"endDate":{},"genres":["Comedy","Ecchi","Romance","Sci-Fi"],"id":192867,"meanScore":63,"popularity":11058,"rankings":[{"allTime":false,"context":"highest rated","format":"TV_SHORT","rank":1,"type":"RATED","year":2026},{"allTime":false,"context":"most popular","format":"TV_SHORT","rank":1,"type":"POPULAR","year":2026},{"allTime":false,"context":"highest rated","format":"TV_SHORT","rank":1,"season":"WINTER","type":"RATED","year":2026},{"allTime":false,"context":"most popular","format":"TV_SHORT","rank":1,"season":"WINTER","type":"POPULAR","year":2026}],"recommendations":{"edges":[{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/162780-rZ0KpsfCg2IA.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#5da1e4","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx162780-brAdNEROhZdG.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx162780-brAdNEROhZdG.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx162780-brAdNEROhZdG.jpg"},"description":"Hiiragi Utena is a major fangirl of the magical girls protecting her city, so when she has the chance to become one herself, she leaps at the chance to join their technicolor ranks… but when she transforms, she learns she isn’t fated to be a daring do-gooder, but rather a villain on the side of evil! At first she tries to quit her new gig as the leader of the local baddies, but she quickly realizes she enjoys it and is a total natural at tormenting the magical girls she loves so much. With both a bang and a whimper, Hiragi’s journey as a magical-girl-tormenting sadist has begun!\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: HIDIVE)","episodes":13,"format":"TV","id":162780,"idMal":54722,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":74,"season":"WINTER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/162780","startDate":{"day":3,"month":1,"year":2024},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Gushing Over Magical Girls","native":"魔法少女にあこがれて","romaji":"Mahou Shoujo ni Akogarete","userPreferred":"Mahou Shoujo ni Akogarete"},"trailer":{"id":"hOgF0D8Pcjs","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hOgF0D8Pcjs/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"coverImage":{"color":"#f1935d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx177509-LzpyXGnjitvF.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx177509-LzpyXGnjitvF.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx177509-LzpyXGnjitvF.jpg"},"description":"This risque romantic comedy story centers on Eita, an introvert mecha otaku high schooler who has a crush on the school's most popular girl Makina. When Eita finds Makina at her doorstep, he is flustered, and even more so when Makina reveals her secret: that she is a \"sexaroid\" robot designed for pleasure, and she is asking Eita to conduct some repairs on her discreetly. While Makina immediately tries to make a move on Eita physically, Eita struggles to contain himself, while also hiding her secret. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\n(Source: Anime News Network, edited)","episodes":12,"format":"TV_SHORT","id":177509,"idMal":58833,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":52,"season":"SPRING","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/177509","startDate":{"day":7,"month":4,"year":2025},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Kakushite! Makina-san!","native":"かくして！ マキナさん!!","romaji":"Kakushite! Makina-san!!","userPreferred":"Kakushite! Makina-san!!"},"trailer":{"id":"Fwjexo4eJ70","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Fwjexo4eJ70/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/21116-ZW9tJtFd7lWm.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#e44386","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx21116-wvQsXTMU3QDg.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx21116-wvQsXTMU3QDg.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx21116-wvQsXTMU3QDg.png"},"description":"After adorable “mermaid” Mamori is transferred to one of five artificial islands, she’s cornered, attacked and eventually saved by another beautiful transfer named Mirei. Unfortunately, even after the girl intervenes, Mamori’s attackers refuse to let up. Just when they think all hope is lost, Mirei and Mamori share a passionate kiss that turns the little “mermaid” into a powerful sword.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: FUNimation)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":21116,"idMal":30385,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":55,"season":"FALL","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/21116","startDate":{"day":10,"month":10,"year":2015},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Valkyrie Drive: Mermaid","native":"ヴァルキリードライヴ マーメイド","romaji":"Valkyrie Drive: Mermaid","userPreferred":"Valkyrie Drive: Mermaid"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/184591-ZD4xr3QagPf2.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#35bbe4","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx184591-jRXZ29bN61Zc.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx184591-jRXZ29bN61Zc.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx184591-jRXZ29bN61Zc.jpg"},"description":"Renako Amaori is leaving her awkward and lonely junior high school life behind, determined to become a normal girl with normal friends in high school. Glamorous, confident Mai Ouzuka is Renako’s total opposite: wealthy, outgoing, and a literal fashion model. Against the odds, the two girls form an immediate connection. Renako thinks she may have found the best friend of her dreams…until Mai’s romantic confession sends her into a tailspin. Renako wants to prove to Mai that being BFFs is better than being girlfriends, but Mai is dead set on convincing Renako that they’re destined to be lovers. Let the love games begin!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\n(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":184591,"idMal":60326,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":76,"season":"SUMMER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/184591","startDate":{"day":8,"month":7,"year":2025},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"There's No Freaking Way I'll Be Your Lover! Unless…","native":"わたしが恋人になれるわけないじゃん、ムリムリ! (※ムリじゃなかった!?)","romaji":"Watashi ga Koibito ni Nareru Wake Naijan, Murimuri! (※Muri ja Nakatta!?)","userPreferred":"Watashi ga Koibito ni Nareru Wake Naijan, Murimuri! (※Muri ja Nakatta!?)"},"trailer":{"id":"nEj2X9x9M7Q","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nEj2X9x9M7Q/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n59-A3U3L90yUEWQ.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#5daef1","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx59-0J95ZHgt4uyP.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx59-0J95ZHgt4uyP.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx59-0J95ZHgt4uyP.jpg"},"description":"In the future, personal computers have developed into \"Persocoms\", mobile computers that look like human beings. Hideki Motosuwa, a prep school student, desperately wants to buy a Persocom but cannot afford to. One day he finds a Persocom that has been thrown away and decides to keep it. When he turns on the Persocom, all she can say is \"Chii\" so he decides to name her that. After a while it starts to become apparent that Chii is more than an average Persocom. Having much better performance, it seems that Chii might be a \"Chobit\", a type of advanced Persocom rumored to have independent thought.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","episodes":26,"format":"TV","id":59,"idMal":59,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":71,"season":"SPRING","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/59","startDate":{"day":3,"month":4,"year":2002},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Chobits","native":"ちょびっツ","romaji":"Chobits","userPreferred":"Chobits"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"coverImage":{"color":"#d61a5d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx21511-D0tPX9spNPQW.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx21511-D0tPX9spNPQW.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx21511-D0tPX9spNPQW.png"},"description":"In an age when large-scale natural disasters frequently happen all over the world, when cyborgs and autonomous robots are beginning to appear on the market in technologically advanced nations, and major world powers compete for technology and resources, the divide between rich and poor grows and the future for the poor looks bleak. In this transitional stage, everyone wanders around in a self-indulgent daze and the way out isn't clear... This is the story of how two cybernetically enhanced girls meet.\n","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":21511,"idMal":32214,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":62,"season":"WINTER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/21511","startDate":{"day":8,"month":1,"year":2016},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Pandora in the Crimson Shell Ghost Urn","native":"紅殻のパンドラ","romaji":"Koukaku no Pandora","userPreferred":"Koukaku no Pandora"},"trailer":{"id":"Hn2ZB9v22U4","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Hn2ZB9v22U4/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/159808-hHtK0HhZlyzD.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#f1a15d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx159808-svpzcGb6ig4X.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx159808-svpzcGb6ig4X.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx159808-svpzcGb6ig4X.jpg"},"description":"Three years into her life as a shut-in, vampire Terakomari Gandesblood (Komari for short), awakens to find she’s been appointed as a Commander in the Mulnite Imperial Army! The thing is, her new unit consists solely of belligerent ruffians who revolt against their superiors at the slightest hint of weakness. Although Komari hails from a line of vampires as powerful as they are prestigious, her refusal to drink blood has made her the picture of mediocrity—scrawny, un-coordinated, and inept at magic. With the odds stacked against her, will the help of her trusty (and slightly infatuated) maid Vill be enough for this recluse to blunder her way to success? Or will Komari rue the day she ever left the safety of her room?\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Yen Press)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":159808,"idMal":54103,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":70,"season":"FALL","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/159808","startDate":{"day":7,"month":10,"year":2023},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"The Vexations of a Shut-In Vampire Princess","native":"ひきこまり吸血姫の悶々","romaji":"Hikikomari Kyuuketsuki no Monmon","userPreferred":"Hikikomari Kyuuketsuki no Monmon"},"trailer":{"id":"ZRXaU02kAco","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ZRXaU02kAco/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n14283-Uqy2GeTEjIHy.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#3578e4","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx14283-kLbZyR6Km5mA.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx14283-kLbZyR6Km5mA.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx14283-kLbZyR6Km5mA.jpg"},"description":"Friendship is the key to protecting the world.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThat is everyone's wish. Here in a world where science has solved all questions.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThis story is set in Oshima. The happy, carefree 14 year old Akane Isshiki lived a poor, but well loved life together with her reliable little sister, Momo, who does all the housework, and her grandfather, Kenjirou, a genius inventor who only created useless devices. When the weather is clear, they can see the artificial island, Blue Island, across the sea. In the center of that island rises the revolutionary Manifestation Engine, a discovery that solved the world's energy problems.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nIt is a peaceful future, just like everyone dreamed of. One where everyone can smile and be happy...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nBut suddenly, the world is visited by danger. An unknown enemy, the Alone, appear, targeting the Manifestation Engine. As none of their weapons worked and they fell into despair, a lone girl takes a stand wearing a red \"Palette Suit\" which wields a great, hidden power. Before long, allies gather around her to fight.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nAnd their friendship becomes the only hope for saving the world!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":14283,"idMal":14283,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":60,"season":"WINTER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/14283","startDate":{"day":11,"month":1,"year":2013},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Vividred Operation","native":"ビビッドレッド・オペレーション","romaji":"Vividred Operation","userPreferred":"Vividred Operation"},"type":"ANIME"}}}]},"relations":{"edges":[{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/136508-PDMxlD8c5Em1.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e450a1","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx136508-VPiHtLM3t6Zv.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx136508-VPiHtLM3t6Zv.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/small/bx136508-VPiHtLM3t6Zv.jpg"},"description":"Beautiful, brainy Tsuda Akane is indispensable at the robotics manufacturer where she works, but her colleagues never saw her private side. At home, Akane’s a hot mess with an apartment that looks more like a landfill than a living space. When she drunkenly orders a maid to help her tidy up, the lady android who arrives is a horny hottie who’s about to give Akane more service than she bargained for!\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ci\u003eNote: Includes eight extra chapters.\u003c/i\u003e","endDate":{"day":18,"month":12,"year":2025},"format":"MANGA","genres":["Comedy","Ecchi","Romance","Sci-Fi"],"id":136508,"idMal":139899,"isAdult":true,"meanScore":72,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/manga/136508","startDate":{"day":16,"month":7,"year":2021},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Does Android Count as Experience?","Does It Count if Your First Time Is With an Android?","Est-ce qu'un androïde compte pour une première fois ?","안드로이드는 경험인 수에 들어가나요??"],"title":{"english":"Does it Count if You Lose Your Virginity to an Android?","native":"アンドロイドは経験人数に入りますか？？","romaji":"Android wa Keiken Ninzuu ni Hairimasu ka??","userPreferred":"Android wa Keiken Ninzuu ni Hairimasu ka??"},"type":"MANGA"},"relationType":"SOURCE"}]},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/192867","staff":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":172539,"name":{"full":"Teishoku Yakiniku"}},"role":"Original Creator"},{"node":{"id":377280,"name":{"full":"NekoB"}},"role":"Director"},{"node":{"id":377280,"name":{"full":"NekoB"}},"role":"Series Composition"},{"node":{"id":290135,"name":{"full":"Mitsuru Tsukiumi"}},"role":"Character Design"},{"node":{"id":361431,"name":{"full":"Minoru Aota"}},"role":"Art Director"},{"node":{"id":290135,"name":{"full":"Mitsuru Tsukiumi"}},"role":"Color Design"},{"node":{"id":361432,"name":{"full":"Tomohiro Hayashi"}},"role":"Director of Photography"},{"node":{"id":361432,"name":{"full":"Tomohiro Hayashi"}},"role":"Editing"},{"node":{"id":160005,"name":{"full":"Fumihiko Ootera"}},"role":"Sound Director"},{"node":{"id":377279,"name":{"full":"ZincP"}},"role":"Music"},{"node":{"id":377555,"name":{"full":"Komaru Kurikoma"}},"role":"Theme Song Performance (ED)"},{"node":{"id":377279,"name":{"full":"ZincP"}},"role":"Theme Song Lyrics (ED)"},{"node":{"id":377279,"name":{"full":"ZincP"}},"role":"Theme Song Composition (ED)"},{"node":{"id":377279,"name":{"full":"ZincP"}},"role":"Theme Song Arrangement (ED)"}]},"startDate":{"day":10,"month":1,"year":2026},"studios":{"nodes":[{"id":7721,"name":"Nyan Pollution-ω-"}]},"trailer":{"id":"SQAHZWo7x28","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/SQAHZWo7x28/hqdefault.jpg"}}},"updated_at":"2026-02-27T21:33:44.719771+03:00"},"207084":{"value":{"Media":{"averageScore":61,"characters":{"edges":[{"id":560805,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"A middle school student living in Kagami Village. The second daughter of the Higure family and an \"older-sister-child\". While she loves her older sister, she also has a complex toward her sister who can do anything, and possesses both admiration and jealousy. In public, she is prickly, but a child-like side remains, such as increasing her self-esteem through conversations with her pet medaka.","gender":"Female","id":389001,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b389001-cAIt8uqmNzeH.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Akane Higure","native":"日暮紅"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/389001"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":560806,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"The eldest daughter of the Higure family, which is a central bloodline of Kagami Village, and works at Kagami Shrine. At the autumn festival held once a year, she performs rituals as the \"Miko of Momiji-yaki\" and is a symbolic existence of the village. She has an elusive personality and is optimistic, but she is a good older sister who has talent no matter what she does and is admired by many people. She has a chronic illness and had weakened to the point of living in a wheelchair, but after nearly one year of hospitalization, she went into remission and returned to Kagami Village where Akane lives.","gender":"Female","id":389002,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b389002-iXvGzta6ZYV5.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Sui Higure","native":"日暮翠"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/389002"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":560807,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"A visitor who came to Kagami Village, where the legend of \"the look-alike\" was being rumored in the streets, and who belongs to an occult research society.","gender":"Female","id":389003,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b389003-Rhq2YhhsvBCm.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Mari","native":"鞠"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/389003"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":560829,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"The Higure family dog.","id":389038,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b389038-zoww2mAIivC0.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Onigiri","native":"オニギリ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/389038"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":560808,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"This character page is set to represent and list credits for voice roles without a specific character name/role attributed. Character roles named specifically should be added separately.","id":36310,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/default.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["その他の登場人物","Others","Additional Voices","Various Voices","Mumei (無名)","Nameless","Non-credit (ノンクレジット)","Yakufumei (役不明)"],"full":"Sonohokasei","native":"その他声"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/36310"},"role":"BACKGROUND"}]},"description":"In the distant future, on the outskirts left behind by the rapid concentration of advanced science and technology in urban areas, lies a remote mountain village known as Kagami Village.\u003cbr/\u003e\n“Behave yourself, or a Double will come for you.”\u003cbr/\u003e\nSuch old folklore still lingers in this village.\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\n\nAkane Higure, a middle school student living in Kagami Village, has been eagerly awaiting the return of her older sister, Sui Higure, who is finally being discharged from the hospital after a year.\u003cbr/\u003e\nHowever, not long after her sister comes home, Akane receives a single phone call.\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\n\n“The girl at home with you… isn’t your sister.”","duration":25,"endDate":{},"genres":["Mystery","Psychological","Supernatural","Thriller"],"id":207084,"meanScore":76,"popularity":744,"rankings":[{"allTime":false,"context":"highest rated","format":"ONA","rank":13,"type":"RATED","year":2026},{"allTime":false,"context":"most popular","format":"ONA","rank":29,"type":"POPULAR","year":2026}],"recommendations":{"edges":[{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/177689-hbCQDYraujAG.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#50aec9","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx177689-d0mB5nYgdnhi.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx177689-d0mB5nYgdnhi.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx177689-d0mB5nYgdnhi.jpg"},"description":"Two best friends living in a rural Japanese village: Yoshiki and Hikaru. Growing up together, they were inseparable… until the day Hikaru came back from the mountains, and was no longer himself. “Something” has taken over Hikaru’s body, memories, feelings… and everything they know begins to unravel.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Netflix)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":177689,"idMal":58913,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":81,"season":"SUMMER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/177689","startDate":{"day":6,"month":7,"year":2025},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"The Summer Hikaru Died","native":"光が死んだ夏","romaji":"Hikaru ga Shinda Natsu","userPreferred":"Hikaru ga Shinda Natsu"},"trailer":{"id":"sFaO07LwAVg","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/sFaO07LwAVg/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n934-p227WvkFZ7XX.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#e4a11a","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx934-wjMlVEl4CWwg.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx934-wjMlVEl4CWwg.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx934-wjMlVEl4CWwg.jpg"},"description":"After moving into the quiet town of Hinamizawa, Maebara Keiichi spends his days blissfully in school often playing games with his local friends. However, appearances can be deceiving. One fateful day, Keiichi stumbles upon news of a murder that had occurred in Hinamizawa. From this point on, horrific events unfold in front of Keiichi, as he soon learns his close friends may not be all that they seem. Based on the amateur mystery game by 07th Expansion, the story is told in a series of different scenarios. ","episodes":26,"format":"TV","id":934,"idMal":934,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":75,"season":"SPRING","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/934","startDate":{"day":5,"month":4,"year":2006},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"When They Cry","native":"ひぐらしのなく頃に","romaji":"Higurashi no Naku Koro ni","userPreferred":"Higurashi no Naku Koro ni"},"trailer":{"id":"PmhjwwY3-f8","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/PmhjwwY3-f8/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/132126-urIgfuSxmxza.jpg","coverImage":{"extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx132126-4ugVjXMQLAps.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx132126-4ugVjXMQLAps.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx132126-4ugVjXMQLAps.png"},"description":"It’s an ordinary summer vacation...except for the fact that Nagara’s high school has mysteriously drifted into another dimension. As the students begin to develop strange new powers, will they work together to survive the alien environment and find a way home, or will their newly formed factions and rivalries turn on each other? \u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Funimation)\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ci\u003eNote: The first episode received an advance release on YouTube on June 19, 2021. The regular TV broadcast started on July 16, 2021.\u003c/i\u003e","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":132126,"idMal":48849,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":78,"season":"SUMMER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/132126","startDate":{"day":16,"month":7,"year":2021},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Sonny Boy","native":"Sonny Boy","romaji":"Sonny Boy","userPreferred":"Sonny Boy"},"trailer":{"id":"k20G56e3OvM","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/k20G56e3OvM/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/155783-MXHfdquIBoHA.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#4386c9","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx155783-YosKbsmZzuDE.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx155783-YosKbsmZzuDE.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx155783-YosKbsmZzuDE.jpg"},"description":"In the year 2024, the world has collapsed. Grotesque monsters lurk amongst the ruins of Japan, while remaining people scrape together what they can to survive. Kiruko, an odd-job girl in Nakano, accepts a mysterious woman's dying wish to take a boy named Maru to a place called Heaven.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Disney+, edited)","episodes":13,"format":"TV","id":155783,"idMal":53393,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":81,"season":"SPRING","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/155783","startDate":{"day":1,"month":4,"year":2023},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Tengoku Daimakyo","native":"天国大魔境","romaji":"Tengoku Daimakyou","userPreferred":"Tengoku Daimakyou"},"trailer":{"id":"Sld5uW_BJU4","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Sld5uW_BJU4/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/154673-aqmmDSHo2IKN.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#f1bb0d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx154673-SCp0Qo62N1Q6.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx154673-SCp0Qo62N1Q6.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx154673-SCp0Qo62N1Q6.jpg"},"description":" New anime project for \u003ci\u003eMECHA-UDE\u003c/i\u003e, as a full-fledged anime series. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nLong ago, alien lifeforms came to Earth, fusing with people on the planet. Due to their appearance, they were dubbed \"Mecha-ude,\" as when fused, they bore a striking resemblance to mechanized limbs.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\nThrough an involuntary partnership, average middle schooler Hikaru Amatsuga works alongside the Mecha-ude Arma, who is an extremely rare and special existence. To protect Arma, the resistance group ARMS assigns the dual Mecha-ude user Aki Murasame to follow him wherever he goes. However, she is also looking for a mysterious Snake-Type Mecha-ude wielder, who has put many of her comrades in a critical state.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\nBehind the scenes, an organization known as the Kagami Group is searching for the mythical \"Trigger Arm,\" a Mecha-ude said to grant unlimited power. When Aki's life is threatened by this group, Hikaru must team up with Arma to find the courage to fight back and, along the way, learn that his life will never be ordinary again. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: MAL Rewrite)","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":154673,"idMal":53033,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":67,"season":"FALL","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/154673","startDate":{"day":4,"month":10,"year":2024},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Mecha Ude: Mechanical Arms","native":"メカウデ (TV)","romaji":"Mecha-ude (TV)","userPreferred":"Mecha-ude (TV)"},"trailer":{"id":"ouqvbqTcBzI","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ouqvbqTcBzI/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/11285-Df7jlyUN8Loc.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#d6ae6b","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx11285-uO6GgQUjikbf.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx11285-uO6GgQUjikbf.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx11285-uO6GgQUjikbf.jpg"},"description":"It isn't the world you know. There wanders a girl with jet-black hair, ebony clothes, and a strikingly blue, glowing eye. Her name is Black\u0026#9733;Rock Shooter. With a huge cannon in hand, she throws herself into a fierce battle...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nMeanwhile, in another world, middle-school student Mato Kuroi is drawn to Yomi Takanashi, her classmate with an unusual family name. Mato does her best to talk to Yomi, who just won't open up. Yu Koutari mocks her best friend Mato's efforts but at the same time, supports her. Mato also finds herself surrounded by other colorful characters at school, like the eccentric school counselor, Saya Irino, and the hot-blooded captain of her club club, Arata Kohata.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThen, one day, the window of opportunity opens. After Mato sees that Yomi has her favorite picture book, \"Li'l Birds At Play\", they strike up a conversation and Mato is invited to come over to Yomi's house. There, they gradually break the ice, until a girl in a wheelchair appears. This is Yomi's best friend, Kagari Izuriha...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nTwo worlds. Mato and Black\u0026#9733;Rock Shooter. This is the story of their \"pain\".\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Nico Nico Douga) ","episodes":8,"format":"TV","id":11285,"idMal":11285,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":63,"season":"WINTER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/11285","startDate":{"day":3,"month":2,"year":2012},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Black Rock Shooter","native":"ブラック★ロックシューター (TV)","romaji":"Black★Rock Shooter (TV)","userPreferred":"Black★Rock Shooter (TV)"},"trailer":{"id":"zN9gcAgn9u0","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/zN9gcAgn9u0/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/20541-n6cLsccx46Jp.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#e4a150","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx20541-vEenrRZqApRn.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx20541-vEenrRZqApRn.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx20541-vEenrRZqApRn.jpg"},"description":"The incidents which occurred on August 14th and 15th bring a group of young boys and girls together… They are members of a group they call themselves the “Mekakushi Dan” (Blindfold Organization) and each member possesses a strange power involving their eyes. Will the members of this peculiar organization be able to solve the mysteries behind these incidents and see the truth?\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Aniplex USA)\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003eA story based on the new popular series of songs by Jin (Shizen no Teki-P) titled \"Kagerou Project\".","episodes":12,"format":"TV","id":20541,"idMal":21603,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":66,"season":"SPRING","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/20541","startDate":{"day":13,"month":4,"year":2014},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"native":"メカクシティアクターズ","romaji":"Mekakucity Actors","userPreferred":"Mekakucity Actors"},"trailer":{"id":"J4KkvN2qipg","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/J4KkvN2qipg/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/180746-AyfiOMkuHegF.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#50c9fe","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx180746-eqDiHbzoHMFh.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx180746-eqDiHbzoHMFh.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx180746-eqDiHbzoHMFh.jpg"},"description":"At just seventeen, Yuki is a professional death game player. She’s survived enough rounds to know that survival is calculation, not luck—and that failure is final. For most players, the games are a nightmare with no escape. For Yuki, they’re simply business. Yet in a world where rooms turn into graves and every choice could be her last, even experience offers no protection.\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Crunchyroll)\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ci\u003eNote: The first episode aired with a runtime of ~47 minutes as opposed to the standard 24 minute long episode.\u003c/i\u003e","episodes":11,"format":"TV","id":180746,"idMal":59711,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":75,"season":"WINTER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/180746","startDate":{"day":7,"month":1,"year":2026},"status":"RELEASING","title":{"english":"SHIBOYUGI: Playing Death Games to Put Food on the Table","native":"死亡遊戯で飯を食う。","romaji":"Shibou Yuugi de Meshi wo Kuu.","userPreferred":"Shibou Yuugi de Meshi wo Kuu."},"trailer":{"id":"rqp_JkzslnM","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/rqp_JkzslnM/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}}]},"relations":{},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/207084","staff":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":146174,"name":{"full":"Harumaki Gohan"}},"role":"Director"},{"node":{"id":146174,"name":{"full":"Harumaki Gohan"}},"role":"Script"},{"node":{"id":146174,"name":{"full":"Harumaki Gohan"}},"role":"Theme Song Composition (OP)"},{"node":{"id":146174,"name":{"full":"Harumaki Gohan"}},"role":"Theme Song Lyrics (OP)"},{"node":{"id":110205,"name":{"full":"Miku Hatsune"}},"role":"Theme Song Performance (OP)"},{"node":{"id":146174,"name":{"full":"Harumaki Gohan"}},"role":"Theme Song Arrangement (OP)"},{"node":{"id":389043,"name":{"full":"ozumikan"}},"role":"Background Art (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":338754,"name":{"full":"Kuen"}},"role":"Background Art (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":304089,"name":{"full":"Oyuhi Kagen"}},"role":"Background Art (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":360957,"name":{"full":"Yoshigoi"}},"role":"Background Art (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":146174,"name":{"full":"Harumaki Gohan"}},"role":"Background Art (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":299448,"name":{"full":"Hajime Minomi"}},"role":"Key Animation (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":205980,"name":{"full":"Shannon"}},"role":"Key Animation (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":174895,"name":{"full":"Ogaki"}},"role":"Key Animation (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":338753,"name":{"full":"Haruyoshi Nagae"}},"role":"Key Animation (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":226491,"name":{"full":"Oomoji no R"}},"role":"Key Animation (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":146174,"name":{"full":"Harumaki Gohan"}},"role":"Key Animation (ep 1)"},{"node":{"id":279307,"name":{"full":"Bakui"}},"role":"Key Animation (ep 1)"}]},"startDate":{"day":31,"month":1,"year":2026},"studios":{"nodes":[{"id":6568,"name":"Studio Gohan"}]},"trailer":{"id":"Asmti3OS0W0","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Asmti3OS0W0/hqdefault.jpg"}}},"updated_at":"2026-03-07T00:36:09.285489+03:00"},"21":{"value":{"Media":{"averageScore":88,"characters":{"edges":[{"id":8805,"node":{"age":"17-","dateOfBirth":{"day":1,"month":4},"description":"__Height:__ 174 cm (5'8½\")\n__Affiliation:__ Straw Hat Pirates (previously Usopp Pirates)  \n__Position:__ Sniper  \n__Bounty:__  ~!500,000,000 (previously 30,000,000 as Sogeking, 200,000,000 as God Usopp)!~  \n \nUsopp is a liar and likes to play pranks on his crew members or just goof off with [Luffy](https://anilist.co/character/40/Luffy-Monkey) and [Chopper](https://anilist.co/character/309). He loves to tell tall tales to Chopper (who believes him blindly) or anyone who's listening. The other aspect of Usopp besides his lying is his cowardice; he is a very timid person, or so he thinks. In extremely stressful situations, Usopp has proven to be far more courageous than he believes himself to be. He shows great resolve when his friends are threatened or mocked by outsiders. Even though he is a complete coward in battle, he is a useful part to the Straw Hat Pirates. He is extremely handy and can fix almost anything. He sometimes sees a role model in [Zoro](https://anilist.co/character/62/Zoro-Roronoa) who never seems afraid but always proud. Usopp lacks a bit of self esteem and is often taken advantage of by Nami to make her weapons or repair and improve them - something he is very adept at, having constructed the ingenious weapon \"Clima Tact.\" \n\nUsopp will also stand up and fight for not only the well-being of people, but also for their ideals - and the ideals of a pirate, which he holds very high. In battle he normally tries to trick his enemy by telling tales or mischievous lies to deceive them. Despite his lack of physical strength compared to other members of the crew, Usopp seems to be just as resilient as his comrades and this ability to bear loads and loads of damage, is one of his best traits, in addition to his cunning and intelligence, which has saved the Straw Hats on many occasions. Usopp also has outstanding marksmanship abilities with his slingshot and is on his way to becoming one of the best snipers in the One Piece world, although his goal in life is to become a proud and strong pirate like his father [Yasopp](https://anilist.co/character/9562/Yasopp) of the Red Haired Pirate Crew.","gender":"Male","id":724,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b724-GFGgI9AJQkfy.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Long-Nose","Usohachi","Usoland","Sogeking","Lysop"],"full":"Usopp","native":"ウソップ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/724"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":14989,"node":{"age":"19-","dateOfBirth":{"day":11,"month":11},"description":"__Height:__ 178 cm (5'10\")\n__Affiliation:__ ~!Straw Hat Pirates (current); Kuraigane Island (former, temporary); Shimotsuki Village (former)!~\n__Bounty:__  ~!1,111,000,000 (previously: 60,000,000, 120,000,000 and 320,000,000)!~\n\nZoro was the first crew member to be recruited by [Luffy](https://anilist.co/character/40/Luffy-Monkey). \n\nZoro is a skilled swordsman who fights with his own unique sword style known as santoryu (three katana fighting style). This is achieved by using one katana in each hand, and another in his mouth. He is also seen fighting with only one or two swords. When in a serious fight he ties his normally, tied on the arm bandana, on his head. Though not a samurai, he appears to maintain a certain degree of bushido, and is frequently mistaken for one. Unlike Luffy and most of the other Straw Hat pirates, Zoro has been known to kill his opponents if he has to, though never in cold blood. \n\nZoro has a stern, serious and distanced personality, however he often reacts in a goofy and exaggerated comic style due to his gruff, impatient attitude. On the ship, he normally either trains with weights or sleeps. The only work he is seen doing regularly is hoisting the anchor using his great strength. He also likes sake, almost to the degree that Luffy likes meat, but like [Nami](https://anilist.co/character/723/Nami), he never gets drunk due to his inhumanly-high endurance and tolerance for alcohol. Another notable trait is his lack of orientation, as Zoro often gets lost, even in small, familiar spaces or when being led by someone. Despite this, he is often the first to sense an enemy or danger, and the first to react. He is often displayed being well aware of dangerous situations and people around him.  \n\nZoro often reminds others of the harsh facts, which often shocks some of the other crew members, although they usually decide he is right. Zoro has also stated that he is an atheist, and has never believed in anything except himself. He often comes across as arrogant and overconfident, but only because he knows he's a strong man with great fighting ability. Even so, Zoro knows that he still has a lot of untapped potential, and is constantly seen training and trying to improve his fighting skills. He adheres to a strict sword master's code of honor, and never falsely brags or lies about his abilities, sometimes outright admitting a weakness, even to an enemy. He also never tries to escape from a fight or use trickery to win, believing that doing so is cowardly and scorning anyone who uses such tactics. Zoro is very vigorous, strong-willed, and determined.","gender":"Male","id":62,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b62-S7oAeA9WInjV.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Zolo","Pirate Hunter","Marimo Head","Mr. Bushido","Zorojuro","Moss Head","Lorenor Zorro"],"full":"Zoro Roronoa","native":"ロロノア・ゾロ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/62"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":15397,"node":{"age":"15-","dateOfBirth":{"day":24,"month":12},"description":"__Height:__ 90 cm (2'11¼\")\n__Affiliation:__ Straw Hat Pirates\n__Position:__  Doctor\n__Devil Fruit:__ Hito Hito no Mi (Human Human Fruit)\n__Devil Fruit Type:__ Zoan\n__Bounty:__ ~!1,000 (previously; 50 and 100)!~\n\nChopper is the 6th member to join the Straw Hat Pirates, acting as their general physician, despite being a reindeer. \n\nAfter a set of unusual circumstances, he ate the Hito Hito no Mi (Human Human Fruit), which permitted him the ability to speak, think, and (to a limited extent) change into a human. Chopper often acts like a child, but he is an upright friend and companion who will try anything to overcome a task given by his team. He also still has distrust in humankind because of events his youth, where he was treated as a brutal monster. He will often outright insult a human who compliments him while smiling, dancing, and being obviously pleased. He also shows a certain interest in books, but mostly medicine related ones. Chopper is more or less on a journey to define himself, seeing almost anybody on his crew as a role model. This, combined with his naiveness, often causes him to imitate the other Straw Hats' actions, no matter how obviously silly. Because of this, he often gets involved in the crazy antics of [Luffy](https://anilist.co/character/40/Luffy-Monkey) and [Usopp](https://anilist.co/character/724/Usopp), wholeheartedly believing that what they are doing is sensible and fun. \n\nChopper is one of the most innocent Straw Hat Pirates, and is also very naive, resulting in a tendency to believe anything told to him, even the outrageously fictitious and exaggerated lies of Usopp. [Sanji](https://anilist.co/character/305/Sanji) originally wanted to cook Chopper and continues to refer to him as \"the emergency food supply\" to tease him but considers him a friend. Although he is the crew's doctor, he wasn't originally hired by Luffy for that purpose, but rather, in Luffy's words, for being  \"a cool reindeer that can transform\".","gender":"Male","id":309,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b309-H64NhbJ2ywIQ.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Tanuki","Chopperman","Cotton Candy Lover","Racoon Dog","Chobro","Chopa-emon  (チョッパえもん)","Chopperemon"],"full":"Chopper Tony Tony","native":"トニートニー・チョッパー"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/309"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":9778,"node":{"age":"18-","dateOfBirth":{"day":3,"month":7},"description":"__Height:__ 169 cm (5'6½”)\n__Affiliation:__ Straw Hat Pirates\n__Position:__  Navigator\n__Bounty:__  ~!366,000,000 (previously; 16,000,000 and 66,000,000)!~\n\nNami is the third person to align herself with Straw Hat Pirates, and the fifth to actually join as an official member. Possibly one of the best navigators currently sailing the Grand Line, she has the ability to recognize and analyze even the slightest changes in the weather through sheer intuition, thus saving the ship and the crew from the very unstable Grand Line weather on multiple occasions.  ","gender":"Female","id":723,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b723-vp5hPptgnNEC.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Cat Burglar","O-Nami","Namizo","Namiland"],"full":"Nami","native":"ナミ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/723"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":15676,"node":{"age":"28-","dateOfBirth":{"day":6,"month":2},"description":"__Height:__ 188 cm (6'2\")\n__Affiliation:__ ~!Straw Hat Pirates (Current); Baltigo (Revolutionaries, Former, Temporary); Alabasta (Baroque Works, Former); Ohara (Former)!~\n__Position:__ Archaeologist\n__Devil Fruit:__  ~!Hana Hana no Mi (Flower Flower Fruit)!~\n__Devil Fruit Type:__ ~!Paramecia!~\n__Bounty:__ ~!930,000,000 (previously; 79,000,000, 80,000,000 and 130,000,000)!~\n\nRobin is the seventh member of Straw Hat's Crew. She had a bounty of 79 million beri (One Piece currency) since she was eight years old, during an incident in which she supposedly destroyed six Buster Call ships through the use of the powers she gained by eating the Hana Hana no Mi (Flower Flower or Blooming Blooming Fruit). The fruit's power enables her to conjure up multiple replicas of her body parts (most often her arms) upon any surface she is able to see making her very powerful and dexterous as a result. Robin joined the Straw Hat Pirates after Luffy saved her life, or (how she states it) Luffy forced her to live when she wanted to die. To atone for his crime, Robin demands that Luffy allow her to join his crew, to which he complies leaving every other crew member except Sanji in shock. Although feared at first, she is quickly accepted and viewed as a comrade by the crew.  Robin is actually an archaeologist of talent and despises anyone who thoughtlessly damages any piece of history. The World Government fears her because she can decipher Poneglyphs (stones marked with glyphs from an ancient language), which contain details capable of reviving ancient weapons that have the power to destroy the world. In reality, Robin has stated that she does not care about ancient weapons and that her dream is to find the True History written on the Rio Poneglyph.  Robin is a mysterious and serious person who appears quiet and reclusive, and the wisest in the Straw Hat's Crew. She was thought by those around her to be cold and mean, but it was proven that she is actually a kind person who always thinks before she acts. She often only speaks when something interesting or important has happened. She loves to study history, and the comfort and freedom to study and read. She is also quick to point out gross or realistically morbid facts, often creeping out Nami or Usopp. Robin is the wisest and most sensible member of the crew. She has a vast knowledge of the seas and the world and usually keeps her head during surprising situations, allowing her to logically analyze the situation without losing her cool. This trait makes her different from the other Straw Hats, who often comically react melodramatically to unexpected happenings and hold irrational ideas and conclusions. Despite her attempts to keep herself distant, Robin has fallen for her new friends and has taken the role of the distant den mother.","gender":"Female","id":61,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b61-ywXUyyocEEqt.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Demon Child","Miss All Sunday","Light of the Revolution","O-Robi","Robiland","Ms. Sunday","Devil Child"],"full":"Robin Nico","native":"ニコロビン"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/61"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":9680,"node":{"age":"17-","dateOfBirth":{"day":5,"month":5},"description":"__Height:__ 172 cm\n__Affiliations:__ ~!Straw Hat Pirates (Captain); Four Emperors!~ \n__Devil Fruit:__ Gomu Gomu no Mi (Rubber-Rubber Fruit) \n__Devil Fruit Type:__ Paramecia\n~!__True Devil Fruit:__ Hito Hito no Mi Model: Nika (Human-Human Fruit)\n__True Devil Fruit Type:__ Mythical Zoan!~\n__Bounty:__ ~!3,000,000,000 (previously: 1,500,000,000, 500,000,000, 400,000,000, 300,000,000, 100,000,000 and 30,000,000)!~\n\nLuffy is the captain of the Straw Hat Pirates and is best friends with all of them and values them over all else. At first glance, Luffy does not appear to be very intelligent, often seeing things in childish manner and can easily be amazed by the simplest things. However, because he views the world in a straightforward and simple manner, he is occasionally the only person who can see past the events and see what should be done.  \n\nLuffy seems to have an unstoppable appetite, a characteristic that is common to the Japanese archetype of the (at times simple-minded) young adventurer with a heart of gold; perhaps the hunger more so in Luffy's case due to having an elastic stomach. Luffy is also another one of the several characters given the middle initial \"D\".  \n\nAlthough Luffy is fairly lightheaded and a funny character, he has an unstoppable sense of determination, optimism and commitment and will do anything to stand up for his friends and comrades. Along with that, he has great courage to back it up as well as unbelievable strength. Ever since consuming the devil fruit he was shown to be not worried about his inability to swim, much like his brother. Much of these traits are common among D's. His only display of true fear is towards his grandfather, to the point that he does not fight back and is intimidated at the mere mention of him.  \n\nLuffy never kills any of the villains, no matter how cold-hearted they are; instead, he frequently sends the villain flying, knocking them out or until the point that they are almost near death, which results in some of the villains searching for revenge, such as Buggy the Clown and Alvida. Author Eiichiro Oda explains that it's not a question of morality so much as a matter of punishing the villains for their crimes - he feels that killing the villains lets them off too lightly, whereas he considers letting them live to see their dreams be ruined a far more fitting punishment.  \n\nLuffy has a dream, and to even have a chance at achieving this dream, he says that he must find the One Piece and become King of the Pirates. He knows that to achieve his goal, he will have to defeat many strong opponents, including the World Government and his childhood hero Shanks. ","gender":"Male","id":40,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b40-MNypXsxSRb1R.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Straw Hat","Mugiwara","Straw","Mugi","Lucy","Luffyland","Mugiwara no Luffy","Mugiwara-ya","Ruffy","Monkey D. Rufy","Rufy","Rubber"],"full":"Luffy Monkey","native":"モンキー・D・ルフィ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/40"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":15189,"node":{"age":"19-","dateOfBirth":{"day":2,"month":3},"description":"__Height:__ 177 cm (5'9\")\n__Affiliation:__ ~!Straw Hat Pirates (current); Momoiro Island (former, temporary); Baratie (former); Germa Kingdom (former)!~\n__Bounty:__ ~!1,032,000,000 (previously; 77,000,000, 177,000,000 (Only Alive) and 330,000,000)!~\n\nSanji is the chain-smoking chef of the Straw Hat Pirate Crew. He has superb fighting skills that only make use of his legs, in an effort to minimize damage to his hands which would impair his cooking skills. Sanji uses an array of powerful and varied kicking moves when he fights. His cooking skills are world class, and he was mentored in both cooking and fighting by Chef \"Red Leg\" Zeff of the Baratie. He was born in the North Blue, but grew up in the East Blue. Sanji is trash-talking and serious, and usually gruff and impatient, especially around men. This is contrasted by his \"love-cook\" side, as he is very amorous around women. Sanji is completely devoted to any beautiful woman, usually losing all common sense and composure in front of them, then attempting to comically swoon them. He has sworn to never let insult or injury happen to any woman while he can still stand, even if that woman is trying to kill him. This is often problematic in his fighting as he can't attack female opponents, and would rather die than hurt them. All this is apparently the result of a \"strict upbringing\".\n\nHis goal in life is to find the All Blue, a legendary ocean, which contains all the fish in the world. As such, it would be paradise for any cook with as much love for his work as Sanji, who holds great respect for the tools, ingredients, and art of cooking. So great is his devotion to his calling, that Sanji will not let any person or creature starve, regardless of them being friend or foe.  Being the crew's chef, he looks out for the health of his crew mates. Sanji respects [Luffy](https://anilist.co/character/40) as a captain, but often gets angry at him for eating too much, showing disrespect for the aesthetics of cooking, and generally being daft and irresponsible. He is constantly in petty fights with [Zoro](https://anilist.co/character/62) (sometimes calling him Marimo) over each others' traits and they have developed a rivalry, but have managed to make a devastating team together. He is very protective of the female crew members and [Nami](https://anilist.co/character/723) likes to take advantage of him, exploiting his extreme servility. Sanji originally wanted to cook [Chopper](https://anilist.co/character/309), but has come to respect him as a crew member and friend. He's also good friends with [Usopp](https://anilist.co/character/724); they team up and interact often, and Sanji understands him quite well. ","gender":"Male","id":305,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b305-6lisPmHtCnLT.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Black Leg","Mr. Prince","Love Cook","Ero Cook","Curly Eyebrows","O-Soba Mask","Sangoro","Mr. Nosebleed","San-gorou"],"full":"Sanji","native":"サンジ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/305"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":15769,"node":{"age":"34-","dateOfBirth":{"day":9,"month":3},"description":"__Height:__ 225cm (7'4½\")\n__Affiliation:__ Straw Hat Pirates (previously; Franky Family, Tom's Workers)\n__Position:__ Shipwright\n__Devil Fruit:__ None\n__Bounty:__  ~!394,000,000 (previously; 44,000,000 and 94,000,000)!~\n\nFranky is a cyborg who is the shipwright of the Straw Hat Pirates. He first appeared in the Water 7 arc. Franky is one of \"Tom's Workers\".  Franky's dream is to build a ship that would travel to the end of the Grand Line. This is the ship that the Straw Hats are currently riding, but his dream is not yet achieved until they make it to the end.  Franky usually acts tough and is quickly angered, but he is also very emotional when it comes to sad tales and often bursts into large tears, or on some occasions, plays a song. His most distinguishable personality trait is his flamboyant attitude. He frequently shouts the word 'SUPER' when he's in a positive mood, or adds it into his speech. He also has a signature pose which he uses very often.  Franky is quick to defend other people (eg. Franky Family, Nico Robin) and take action if his friends are harmed. He is also quick in making friends, allies, and comrades with even the most unlikely of individuals. Because of this, he is seen as a 'big brother' figure. Monkey D. Luffy bears similar qualities (with the exception of engaging in unnecessary fights) and because of this, despite the disputes the two had in the past, both grew to respect each other during the events of the Enies Lobby Arc.","gender":"Male","id":64,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/n64-ChX6ZzHHjXqA.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Cyborg","Bakanky","Iron Man","Fraland","Franosuke","Frankie"],"full":"Franky","native":"フランキー"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/64"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":45118,"node":{"age":"44-","dateOfBirth":{"day":2,"month":4},"description":"__Height:__ 301 cm (9'10½\")\n__Affiliation:__ ~!Straw Hat Pirates (current); Sun Pirates (former); Ally of the Big Mom Pirates (former); Shichibukai (former); Ryugu Kingdom (resigned); Impel Down (former)]!~\n__Position:__ ~!Captain (Sun Pirates), Helmsman (Straw Hat Pirates)!~\n__Devil Fruit:__ None\n__Bounty:__ ~!1,100,000,000 (previously; 250,000,000, 76,000,000 and 438,000,000)!~\n\nJinbe is a whale shark fishman who was the second captain of the Sunny Pirates after Fisher Tiger, and who became a Shichibukai eight years ago. Jinbe's name comes from jinbei-zame (甚平鮫), which means \"whale shark\" in Japanese. His epithet, Kaikyou would normally translate into \"Strait\" or \"Channel\". However since the kanji for it is written as (海侠の) and not (海峡の), the kyou part (侠) of it comes from (任侠), a honorific used when addressing a high ranking yakuza member, thus making his epithet a Japanese pun.\n\n(Source: One Piece Wikia) ","gender":"Male","id":18938,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b18938-yZANEfjsVhW4.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Kaikyou no Jinbe","Knight of the Sea","First Son of the Sea","Jimbei","Jinbei","Jinbee","Boss Jinbe"],"full":"Jinbe","native":"ジンベエ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/18938"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":49630,"node":{"age":"88-","dateOfBirth":{"day":3,"month":4},"description":"__Height:__ 266 cm (8'8½\")\n__Affiliation:__ Straw Hat Pirates (previously; Rumbar Pirates)\n__Position:__ Musician, Swordsman\n__Devil Fruit:__ Yomi Yomi no Mi (Revive Revive Fruit)\n__Devil Fruit Type:__ Paramecia\n__Bounty:__  ~!383,000,000 (previously; 33,000,000 and 83,000,000)!~\n\nBrook known as the \"Gentleman Skeleton\", is a pirate inhabiting the Florian Triangle region of the Grand Line. Although he claims to be a gentleman, and talks in the dialect of one, Brook's etiquette has severely degenerated over the course of his isolation. He has awful table manners: he shouts for food while waiting to be served, asks to swap plates with people who have larger servings than he does and eating so messily his entire face is stained. He is also extremely flatulent after meals, but says \"excuse me\" so as to be \"gentlemanly.\" He also loves to tell odd, bone-themed jokes, as well as melodramatic tales, and is very perverted, asking to see Nami and Robin's underwear upon meeting them.   He's a skilled musician (something Luffy has always wanted in his crew since the beginning), fond of playing the violin. Due to his light weight he can not only jump to incredible heights but can run on water by moving his legs furiously. He uses a shikomizue as his main weapon; with it, he is able to make swift iaidō attacks that the enemy cannot notice.","gender":"Male","id":5627,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b5627-av8oD3zhKvDl.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Dead Bones","Soul King","Satan-sama","Boneland","Honekichi","Bonekichi","The Starving Skeleton","Humming Brook"],"full":"Brook","native":"ブルック"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/5627"},"role":"MAIN"},{"id":1057,"node":{"age":"28","dateOfBirth":{"day":2,"month":6},"description":"__Height::__ 212 cm (6'11½\")\n__Affiliation:__ Galley-La Company ~!CP9 (former); CP-0!~\n__Devil Fruit:__ Neko Neko no Mi, Model: Leopard (Cat-Cat Fruit Leopard Model)\n__Devil Fruit Type:__ Zoan \n\nWhen Lucci is first seen as one of the five foremen of Galley-La Company's Dock One, he appears to be a ventriloquist using his pigeon, Hattori, to speak for him. He also shows very impressive skills when he gets into a fight with Paulie and, later on, Luffy. \n\n~!It is soon revealed he is the unquestioned leader of the Water 7 CP9 unit which infiltrated the Galley-La company, and perfectly capable of speaking for himself. Lucci ate the Neko Neko no Mi, Model: Leopard (ネコネコの実 モデル豹(レオパルド), Cat Cat Fruit, Model: Leopard ), which allows him to turn into a huge leopard-human hybrid and a full leopard. This coupled with his mastered martial arts style of rokushiki, makes him a resilient foe, and he has been ranked as the strongest CP9 agent by far. Lucci can perform Life Return, like Kumadori, and use it to alter his body into forms that amplify his skills in a specific rokushiki ability, though only Kami-e Form, which makes his man-beast form smaller and thinner, has been seen and arguably the main villain of the Enies Lobby Arc if not the main threat to the Straw Hats at the time.!~ \n\n~!In the anime, Lucci\u0026#039;s backstory to his admission in CP9 is revealed by a Vice Admiral during the Buster Call on Enies Lobby. Fifteen years prior, a kingdom had 500 of its soldiers and its king taken hostage by a pirate crew, with the captain demanding to be made the new king of the kingdom. As the government saw the king beginning to admit defeat, they sent in the then thirteen year-old Rob Lucci, who mercilessly killed all 500 hostages to get to the captain, whom he killed without mercy. During this incident, he gained a back full of scars from the pirate crew\u0026#039;s guns, vaguely scarred in the shape of the World Government\u0026#039;s symbol. Shortly after that he became a CP9 member, and gained the reputation of being the group\u0026#039;s most cold-hearted and efficient assassin in its entire history. As such, he is a very valuable asset to the World Government, almost to the point of legend; the other vice admirals believe that he can even survive a Buster Call attack.    At the Galley-La headquarters in Water 7, Lucci effortlessly defeated Luffy in a relatively short fight. Later in Enies Lobby, Luffy chased after Lucci and initiated a second fight with him. The two engaged in an extremely long, hectic and boisterous fight in which Luffy eventually emerged victorius. Lucci respectively bested, withstood and survived Luffy\u0026#039;s attacks and various states until he was defeated. However, it took Luffy\u0026#039;s last bits of energy to defeat him, as Luffy was in the floor and couldn\u0026#039;t even move. This proves how much of a monster Lucci was, but also how much stronger Luffy has become.!~\n\n~!Lucci comes off as the most cold and collected member of CP9, almost never displaying any emotions. An example is the brutal assault on his friend of five years, Paulie, whom he even tried to kill after the CP9\u0026#039;s identities have been revealed. He also states that he feels no real bond with the city he\u0026#039;s lived in for those five years. He also seems to have no feelings for his fellow CP9 colleagues, least of all Spandam. His emotionless nature includes anger and distress (he\u0026#039;s \u0026quot;kept together\u0026quot; all through his fight with Luffy, unlike all the previous villains). Even while taunting or demoralizing Luffy, he keeps a passive face, and refrains from the classic \u0026quot;villain laugh\u0026quot;. However, during the final moments of his fight with Luffy, he expresses surprise and anger prior to being defeated.  He seems to derive amusement and gratification from inflicting physical and emotional pain on others, making him a typical sadist. These scenes, along with when he anticipates battle, are the only times where he smirks. In Enies Lobby, he reveals that he works so he could be legally allowed to kill people. An example of Lucci\u0026#039;s lust for violence is when he compromised the mission of bringing Robin to the Gates of Justice by allowing Luffy to tail him, for the sole purpose of having a battle. Lucci\u0026#039;s violent and predatory nature is also shown when he goes into full-beast mode during battle, in order to attack Luffy more violently.  However, while Lucci does love the benefits of his job (killing people), he seems to be completely devoted to the government he serves as a tool from the shadows. He speaks of pirates as \u0026quot;evil\u0026quot;, and sees it as his duty to hunt down and eliminate Nico Robin. All this is revealed towards the end of his battle with Luffy, and is a sudden departure from his \u0026quot;care for nothing but blood\u0026quot; attitude. This may be because he was dominating the fight at the time, and his bloodlust, which otherwise overshadows his better judgement, had worn off since Luffy was no longer fun to fight. However, as his flashback in the anime shows, this moral isn\u0026#039;t just limited to pirates. If Lucci sees anybody that he believes faulters in the face of justice, they have \u0026quot;sinned\u0026quot; in his eyes and must be eliminated. This is his own sense of justice which he calls \u0026quot;dark justice\u0026quot;. Lucci also appears to exhibit a rather high level of intelligence. It was he who deduced the connection between Iceburg and Franky, figured out the principles behind Luffy\u0026#039;s Gear 2nd \u0026quot;upgrade\u0026quot;, and showed extensive knowledge about Devil Fruit. On Enies Lobby, he even effortlessly jeopardized the lives of Luffy\u0026#039;s crewmembers and friends, as well as their mission to save Robin, by flooding the underwater passageway to the Gates of Justice. Although this might just as well be yet another display of sadism, where he removes Luffy\u0026#039;s chances of \u0026quot;having everything\u0026quot; just for the sake of angering him. Lucci has a complete mastery of Rokushiki, having not only used at least one or more moves from each of the different forms with ease, but to such an extent that he can mix two or more forms together to great effect. He demonstrates this when he unveils the Rokushiki hidden technique, Rokuougan, during his fight with Luffy. The massively powerful technique, usable only by one who has literally mastered all six forms as stated by Lucci himself, is so strong that it causes severe internal injury to Luffy\u0026#039;s body; no small feat considering he has a rubber body. Luffy described it as if an \u0026#039;Impact Dial\u0026#039; with much more greatly amplified power went off inside his chest. Not much is known about Hattori, the pigeon that is constantly seen perched on Lucci\u0026#039;s shoulder. It appears to have no special significance. While acting as Lucci\u0026#039;s voice Hattori expresses human body language, matching the behavior of a professional shipwright: constantly insulting and lecturing Paulie because of his reckless lifestyle. After the CP9 reveal their identities, Hattori loses many of his human characteristics, although he is seen wearing a coat and drinking from a cocktail glass.!~","gender":"Male","id":5677,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b5677-ZrZunVe7Kq5P.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Pigeon Guy"],"full":"Lucci Rob","native":"ロブ･ルッチ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/5677"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":3712,"node":{"age":"39","dateOfBirth":{"day":4,"month":10},"description":"__Debut:__ Chapter 286; Episode 187 \n__Height:__ 222 cm (7'3\")\n__Origin:__ Grand Line\n\nCalgara was a hero and a warrior of the Shandians who lived while Upper Yard was still a part of Jaya (some 400 years ago), and who befriended the explorer Montblanc Norland (the ancestor of Montblanc Cricket). A statue of him was erected after his death as an eternal reminder to the Shandians of his strength and courage. He had a daughter named Musse. Wiper is a direct descendant of his.    Calgara was quick to react and a strong believer in traditions of his people. He was hugely mistrusting of strangers. Calgara's personality changed after he met Norland with many of his outtakes of the world changing alongside it. One particular note was that after seeing his God for what it truly was (a giant snake), he dismisses all Gods including the Skypieans \u0026quot;God\u0026quot;.","gender":"Male","id":17190,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/n17190-BCsc92WDAZPs.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Karugara","Kalgara","Shandora's Demon"],"full":"Calgara","native":"カルガラ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/17190"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":6680,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"Whetton is a character in the One Piece Rainbow Mist filler arc. He is a former pirate, who burned down Ruluka and then became its mayor, because he yearned for safety and power. He later funds Henzo\u0026#039;s research, by putting up silly and exorbitant taxes, to complete the construction of the Rainbow Tower, so as to get access to the Rainbow Mist\u0026#039;s treasures. \n\n(Source: One Piece Wikia)","id":33569,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/33569.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Mayor"],"full":"Whetton","native":"ウェットン"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/33569"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":9775,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{"day":8,"month":8},"description":"__Affiliations:__ Kuja Pirates\n\nAphelandra is a member of a tribe of Kuja living on the island of Amazon Lily. She is large-sized human who accompanied Marguerite and Sweet Pea when they found Luffy covered in mushrooms. Despite her size, Aphelandra has shown to be rather timid, often repeating what others have said to her as she obeys their command. She is a kind and innocent woman.\n\n","gender":"Female","id":21541,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b21541-Dkm9rWSYxyJE.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Aphelandra","native":"アフェランドラ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/21541"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":10432,"node":{"age":"24-","dateOfBirth":{"day":27,"month":1},"description":"__Height:__ 215 cm (7'0½\")\n__Affiliation:__ Rolling Pirates ~!Charlotte Family!~\n__Bounty:__ ~!24,000,000!~\n\nThe original Lola is a female pirate who is the captain of the Rolling Pirates. She is a member of a group of Moria's victims who have banded together, the Thriller Bark Victim's Association.\n~!She is one of the daughters of Big Mom and her father is Linlin's 25th husband, Pound. She is the younger twin sister of Chiffon!~","gender":"Female","id":35834,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b35834-oKYQTV6tORQT.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Marriage Proposal Lola"],"full":"Lola","native":"ローラ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/35834"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":13460,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{"day":14,"month":1},"description":"Sweet Pea (スイトピー, Suitopī?) is a member of a tribe of Kuja living on the island of Amazon Lily. She was first seen accompanying Marguerite and Aphelandra when they found the mushroom covered Luffy. \n\n(Source: One Piece Wikia)","gender":"Female","id":21540,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b21540-WpdEYB6NddiO.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Sweet Pea","native":"スイトピー"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/21540"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":14987,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"__First Appearance:__ Chapter 161; Episode 96   \n\nThe Kung-Fu Dugongs are a type of Dugong living in Arabasta that is famous for their martial arts skills and strength. Their code of honor states that once they are defeated, a Dugong must become the follower of the one who defeated them. Their code extends to any 'disciples' their master may have with him as well. Currently, their master is Luffy as he unwittingly defeated them all. They live in the Sandora River.  \n\n(Source: One Piece Wikia)","id":18784,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/18784.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Kung Fu Dugong","native":"クンフージュゴン"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/18784"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":15394,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"Enishida (エニシダ, Enishida?) is a member of the Kuja. One of Hancock's attendants in her castle. ","id":21544,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b21544-SUgpMDh6isaf.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Enishida","native":"エニシダ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/21544"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":15770,"node":{"age":"30","dateOfBirth":{"day":9,"month":1},"description":"__Debut:__ Chapter 598; Episode 517 \n__Affiliations:__ Fake Straw Hat Crew \n__Height:__ 294 cm (9'7\") \n\nMounblutain was a member of the Fake Straw Hat Crew who masqueraded as [Sogeking](https://anilist.co/character/724/Usopp).","gender":"Male","id":49821,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b49821-5e0vEA3UME87.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Fake Sogeking"],"full":"Mounblutain","native":"マウンブルテン"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/49821"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":16745,"node":{"age":"16","dateOfBirth":{"day":4,"month":4},"description":"First Appearance: Chapter 612 \n\nA giant smelt-whiting mermaid and the youngest of King Neptune's children. She was first mentioned by Pappug, who claimed he knew her and even promised to introduce her to the Straw Hat Pirates when they arrived at Fishman Island (though later this is revealed to be a lie). ~!She is the Ancient Weapon Poseidon.!~ \n\n(Source: One Piece Wikia)  ","gender":"Female","id":40273,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/40273.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Mermaid Princess","Yowahoshi"],"full":"Shirahoshi","native":"しらほし"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/40273"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":18435,"node":{"age":"27","dateOfBirth":{"day":11,"month":4},"description":"Pekoms is a combatant of the Big Mom Pirates. He is partnered with Tamago, and both are responsible for collecting the monthly payment of sweets from Fishman Island in exchange for Big Mom's protection.   First Appearance: Chapter 651   ~!Bounty: 330,000,000.!~  (source: One Piece Wikia)","gender":"Male","id":54499,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b54499-1Bb8NfHH07Kj.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Pecoms","Mystoms"],"full":"Pekoms","native":"ペコムズ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/54499"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":19868,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"Spandam is the leader of CP9, and the former leader of CP5. As the leader of CP5 he attempted to retrieve the blueprints of the weapon Pluton from the shipwright Tom. He failed, though Tom was imprisoned as a result of Spandam's actions. As the leader of CP9, he ordered the capture of Franky and Nico Robin, and had them taken to Enies Lobby. Spandam is defeated by Nico Robin, who breaks his back while the Straw Hat crew flee the Bridge of Hesitation. He owns a sword, \u0026quot;Funk Freed\u0026quot; (ファンクフリード Fankufurīdo), which \u0026quot;ate\u0026quot; the Devil Fruit, Zou Zou no Mi (ゾウゾウの実 Elephant Elephant Fruit), giving it the ability to transform into an elephant.    Source: Wikipedia","id":6551,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b6551-szpvKXmtWqGX.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Spandam","native":"スパンダム"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/6551"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":21209,"node":{"dateOfBirth":{},"description":"Zeo is a Japanese wobbegong shark fishman and an officer of the New Fishman Pirates.  First Appearance: Chapter 611  (source: One Piece Wikia)","id":40276,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b40276-cDrb69UzdEbp.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Zeo","native":"ゼオ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/40276"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":22886,"node":{"age":"66","dateOfBirth":{"day":22,"month":12},"description":"**First Appearance:** Chapter 237; Episode 153\n\nGan Fall, is the current, two time God of Skypiea.","gender":"Male","id":22798,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b22798-2DOxtVP5YtfT.png"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"alternative":["Sky Knight","Ganfall","Ganfor","Gunfall","Gan Fooru","Sora no Kishi (空の騎士)","Knight of the Sky","Sky Lord"],"full":"Gan Fall","native":"ガン・フォール"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/22798"},"role":"SUPPORTING"},{"id":24017,"node":{"age":"24","dateOfBirth":{"day":4,"month":2},"description":"__Height:__ 604 cm (19’10”)\n__Affiliation:__ Neptune Family\n\nFukaboshi is a shark merman and also the first son of the royal Neptune family on Fishman Island.\n\n","gender":"Male","id":40264,"image":{"large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b40264-jSwDS1UM0nOF.jpg"},"isFavourite":false,"name":{"full":"Fukaboshi","native":"フカボシ"},"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/character/40264"},"role":"SUPPORTING"}]},"description":"Gold Roger was known as the Pirate King, the strongest and most infamous being to have sailed the Grand Line. The capture and death of Roger by the World Government brought a change throughout the world. His last words before his death revealed the location of the greatest treasure in the world, One Piece. It was this revelation that brought about the Grand Age of Pirates, men who dreamed of finding One Piece (which promises an unlimited amount of riches and fame), and quite possibly the most coveted of titles for the person who found it, the title of the Pirate King.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nEnter Monkey D. Luffy, a 17-year-old boy that defies your standard definition of a pirate. Rather than the popular persona of a wicked, hardened, toothless pirate who ransacks villages for fun, Luffy’s reason for being a pirate is one of pure wonder; the thought of an exciting adventure and meeting new and intriguing people, along with finding One Piece, are his reasons of becoming a pirate. Following in the footsteps of his childhood hero, Luffy and his crew travel across the Grand Line, experiencing crazy adventures, unveiling dark mysteries and battling strong enemies, all in order to reach One Piece.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cb\u003e*This includes following special episodes:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n- Chopperman to the Rescue! Protect the TV Station by the Shore! (Episode 336)\u003cbr\u003e\n- The Strongest Tag-Team! Luffy and Toriko's Hard Struggle! (Episode 492)\u003cbr\u003e\n- Team Formation! Save Chopper (Episode 542)\u003cbr\u003e\n- History's Strongest Collaboration vs. Glutton of the Sea (Episode 590)\u003cbr\u003e\n- 20th Anniversary! Special Romance Dawn (Episode 907)","duration":24,"endDate":{},"genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy"],"id":21,"meanScore":88,"popularity":666504,"rankings":[{"allTime":true,"context":"highest rated all time","format":"TV","rank":20,"type":"RATED"},{"allTime":true,"context":"most popular all time","format":"TV","rank":10,"type":"POPULAR"},{"allTime":false,"context":"highest rated","format":"TV","rank":1,"type":"RATED","year":1999},{"allTime":false,"context":"most popular","format":"TV","rank":1,"type":"POPULAR","year":1999}],"recommendations":{"edges":[{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/11061-8WkkTZ6duKpq.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#f1d65d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx11061-y5gsT1hoHuHw.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx11061-y5gsT1hoHuHw.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx11061-y5gsT1hoHuHw.png"},"description":"A new adaption of the manga of the same name by Togashi Yoshihiro.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nA Hunter is one who travels the world doing all sorts of dangerous tasks. From capturing criminals to searching deep within uncharted lands for any lost treasures. Gon is a young boy whose father disappeared long ago, being a Hunter. He believes if he could also follow his father's path, he could one day reunite with him.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nAfter becoming 12, Gon leaves his home and takes on the task of entering the Hunter exam, notorious for its low success rate and high probability of death to become an official Hunter. He befriends the revenge-driven Kurapika, the doctor-to-be Leorio and the rebellious ex-assassin Killua in the exam, with their friendship prevailing throughout the many trials and threats they come upon taking on the dangerous career of a Hunter.","episodes":148,"format":"TV","id":11061,"idMal":11061,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":89,"season":"FALL","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/11061","startDate":{"day":2,"month":10,"year":2011},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Hunter x Hunter (2011)","native":"HUNTER×HUNTER (2011)","romaji":"HUNTER×HUNTER (2011)","userPreferred":"HUNTER×HUNTER (2011)"},"trailer":{"id":"d6kBeJjTGnY","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/d6kBeJjTGnY/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/20-HHxhPj5JD13a.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#e47850","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx20-dE6UHbFFg1A5.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx20-dE6UHbFFg1A5.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx20-dE6UHbFFg1A5.jpg"},"description":"Naruto Uzumaki, a hyperactive and knuckle-headed ninja, lives in Konohagakure, the Hidden Leaf village. Moments prior to his birth, a huge demon known as the Kyuubi, the Nine-tailed Fox, attacked Konohagakure and wreaked havoc. In order to put an end to the Kyuubi's rampage, the leader of the village, the 4th Hokage, sacrificed his life and sealed the monstrous beast inside the newborn Naruto. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nShunned because of the presence of the Kyuubi inside him, Naruto struggles to find his place in the village. He strives to become the Hokage of Konohagakure, and he meets many friends and foes along the way. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: MAL Rewrite)","episodes":220,"format":"TV","id":20,"idMal":20,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":80,"season":"FALL","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/20","startDate":{"day":3,"month":10,"year":2002},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Naruto","native":"NARUTO -ナルト-","romaji":"NARUTO","userPreferred":"NARUTO"},"trailer":{"id":"-G9BqkgZXRA","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/-G9BqkgZXRA/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/1735.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#e4865d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx1735-kGfVm0YqCPcu.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx1735-kGfVm0YqCPcu.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx1735-kGfVm0YqCPcu.png"},"description":"Naruto: Shippuuden is the continuation of the original animated TV series Naruto. The story revolves around an older and slightly more matured Uzumaki Naruto and his quest to save his friend Uchiha Sasuke from the grips of the snake-like Shinobi, Orochimaru. After 2 and a half years Naruto finally returns to his village of Konoha, and sets about putting his ambitions to work, though it will not be easy, as he has amassed a few (more dangerous) enemies, in the likes of the shinobi organization; Akatsuki. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","episodes":500,"format":"TV","id":1735,"idMal":1735,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":82,"season":"WINTER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/1735","startDate":{"day":15,"month":2,"year":2007},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Naruto: Shippuden","native":"NARUTO -ナルト- 疾風伝","romaji":"NARUTO: Shippuuden","userPreferred":"NARUTO: Shippuuden"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/97940-1URQdQ4U1a0b.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#d6c96b","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx97940-fyh8o7gNbha0.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx97940-fyh8o7gNbha0.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx97940-fyh8o7gNbha0.png"},"description":"In a world where magic is everything, Asta and Yuno are both found abandoned at a church on the same day. While Yuno is gifted with exceptional magical powers, Asta is the only one in this world without any. At the age of fifteen, both receive grimoires, magic books that amplify their holder’s magic. Asta’s is a rare Grimoire of Anti-Magic that negates and repels his opponent’s spells. Being opposite but good rivals, Yuno and Asta are ready for the hardest of challenges to achieve their common dream: to be the Wizard King. Giving up is never an option!\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Crunchyroll)","episodes":170,"format":"TV","id":97940,"idMal":34572,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":79,"season":"FALL","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/97940","startDate":{"day":3,"month":10,"year":2017},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Black Clover","native":"ブラッククローバー","romaji":"Black Clover","userPreferred":"Black Clover"},"trailer":{"id":"vUjAxk1qYzQ","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vUjAxk1qYzQ/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/223-vyRuUBBYfcUb.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#e48635","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx223-scE5uJfXqqj8.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx223-scE5uJfXqqj8.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx223-scE5uJfXqqj8.png"},"description":"Goku Son is a young boy who lives in the woods all alone—that is until a girl named Bulma runs into him in her search for a set of magical objects called the \"Dragon Balls.\" Since the artifacts are said to grant one wish to whoever collects all seven, Bulma hopes to gather them and wish for a perfect boyfriend. Goku happens to be in possession of a dragon ball, but unfortunately for Bulma, he refuses to part ways with it, so she makes him a deal: he can tag along on her journey if he lets her borrow the dragon ball's power. With that, the two set off on the journey of a lifetime.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\nThey don't go on the journey alone. On the way, they meet the old Muten-Roshi and wannabe disciple Kuririn, with whom Goku trains to become a stronger martial artist for the upcoming World Martial Arts Tournament. However, it's not all fun and games; the ability to make any wish come true is a powerful one, and there are others who would do much worse than just wishing for a boyfriend. To stop those who would try to abuse the legendary power, they train to become stronger fighters, using their newfound strength to help the people around them along the way.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: MAL Rewrite)","episodes":153,"format":"TV","id":223,"idMal":223,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":78,"season":"WINTER","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/223","startDate":{"day":26,"month":2,"year":1986},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Dragon Ball","native":"ドラゴンボール","romaji":"Dragon Ball","userPreferred":"Dragon Ball"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/813-03ZLvWJgR6Wd.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#e49343","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx813-ZhnFNOeCU5dQ.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx813-ZhnFNOeCU5dQ.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx813-ZhnFNOeCU5dQ.png"},"description":"Goku is back with his new son, Gohan, but just when things are getting settled down, the adventures continue. Whether he is facing enemies such as Freeza, Cell, or Boo, Goku is proven to be an elite of his own and discovers his race, Saiyan. He meets many new people, gaining allies as well as enemies, as he still finds time to raise a family and be the happy-go-lucky Saiyan he is.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","episodes":291,"format":"TV","id":813,"idMal":813,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":80,"season":"SPRING","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/813","startDate":{"day":26,"month":4,"year":1989},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Dragon Ball Z","native":"ドラゴンボールZ","romaji":"Dragon Ball Z","userPreferred":"Dragon Ball Z"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/269-08ar2HJOUAuL.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#f1a150","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx269-d2GmRkJbMopq.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx269-d2GmRkJbMopq.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx269-d2GmRkJbMopq.png"},"description":"Ichigo Kurosaki is a rather normal high school student apart from the fact he has the ability to see ghosts. This ability never impacted his life in a major way until the day he encounters the Shinigami Kuchiki Rukia, who saves him and his family's lives from a Hollow, a corrupt spirit that devours human souls. \n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nWounded during the fight against the Hollow, Rukia chooses the only option available to defeat the monster and passes her Shinigami powers to Ichigo. Now forced to act as a substitute until Rukia recovers, Ichigo hunts down the Hollows that plague his town. \n\n\n","episodes":366,"format":"TV","id":269,"idMal":269,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":79,"season":"FALL","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/269","startDate":{"day":5,"month":10,"year":2004},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Bleach","native":"BLEACH","romaji":"BLEACH","userPreferred":"BLEACH"},"trailer":{"id":"0c4IoCA5fY0","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0c4IoCA5fY0/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}},{"node":{"mediaRecommendation":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/6702-VSHyctSAeUBS.jpg","coverImage":{"color":"#e45d50","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b6702-KI4qgSMyI8Pm.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b6702-KI4qgSMyI8Pm.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b6702-KI4qgSMyI8Pm.png"},"description":"Across the Fiore kingdom, wizards join guilds and make their pay by filling magical needs—but one guild has a reputation as the roughest, rowdiest, most dangerous of all: Fairy Tail!\u003cbr\u003e\nWhen four young Fairy Tail members unite, their bond is forged by a power found in neither muscle nor magic and grows stronger with every mission. Whatever you do, don't mess with these friends or you'll get a taste of Natsu's flaming fist or Gray's ice hammer, suffer a painful blow from one of Lucy's celestial spirits or catch the edge of Erza's mighty blade! Whether they're stopping demons from devastating the world or wrestling in the mess hall, this mystical team manages to inflict as much damage to their rivals as they do to the surrounding area!\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Funimation)","episodes":175,"format":"TV","id":6702,"idMal":6702,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":71,"season":"FALL","siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/6702","startDate":{"day":12,"month":10,"year":2009},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"Fairy Tail","native":"FAIRY TAIL","romaji":"FAIRY TAIL","userPreferred":"FAIRY TAIL"},"trailer":{"id":"mAAKPx-ndAg","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mAAKPx-ndAg/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"}}}]},"relations":{"edges":[{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/466-uS8J4XwJ35Ws.png","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e49328","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx466-bVP54I7dCB2F.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx466-bVP54I7dCB2F.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx466-bVP54I7dCB2F.jpg"},"description":"While Luffy and his crew of Zoro and Nami are starving on their small boat, they are attacked by a large monster. Nami is taken away, while Luffy and Zoro wash up on shore. There they meet a young girl, Medaka, and learn of the sad history of the island. The evil Pirate Ganzack has taken away all the men in the village and enslaved them, including Medaka's father. Now Luffy, Zoro, and Medaka must infiltrate Ganzack's base in order to rescue the villagers and Nami. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":28,"endDate":{"day":26,"month":7,"year":1998},"episodes":1,"format":"OVA","genres":["Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":466,"idMal":466,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":64,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":1998,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/466","startDate":{"day":26,"month":7,"year":1998},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Defeat Him! The Pirate Ganzack!","ONE PIECE ジャンプスーパーアニメツアー'98","ONE PIECE Jump Super Anime Tour '98"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Defeat the Pirate Ganzack!","native":"ONE PIECE 倒せ!海賊ギャンザック","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Taose! Kaizoku Ganzack","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Taose! Kaizoku Ganzack"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n1094-IAIqiFbLBsig.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1a10d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx1094-H3YFJ1TR0ZZi.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx1094-H3YFJ1TR0ZZi.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx1094-H3YFJ1TR0ZZi.jpg"},"description":"The Straw Hats encounter a city in the middle of a whirlpool, called the Ocean's Navel, that is being destroyed by giant monsters. These monsters supposedly protect a treasure capable of granting wishes, but in the process of defeating these guardians, the crew ends up releasing another evil.  (aired after Episode 53)\u003cbr\u003e","duration":49,"endDate":{"day":20,"month":12,"year":2000},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":1094,"idMal":1094,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":67,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2000,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/1094","startDate":{"day":20,"month":12,"year":2000},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: Avventura nell'ombelico dell'oceano","One Piece Special: Adventure in the Ocean's Navel","วันพีซ ภาคพิเศษ 1 การผจญภัยใต้มหาสมุทร","Vua Hải Tặc: Cuộc phiêu lưu vào rốn đại dương","One Piece Special: Luffy Falls! Adventure in the Navel of the Sea"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Umi no Heso no Daibouken-hen","native":"ONE PIECE TVスペシャル 海のヘソの大冒険篇","romaji":"ONE PIECE TV Special: Umi no Heso no Daibouken-hen","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE TV Special: Umi no Heso no Daibouken-hen"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n1237-hHWuRsuVsVpr.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4ae35","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/1237.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/1237.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/1237.jpg"},"description":"The story opens on Pirate Zap's ship, where two of his crew, Bonnie and Max, are tired and want to escape, but unfortunately they have no money. Three children were being held captive on the ship overhear them. The eldest, Amanda, who's father was a pro treasure hunter, knows the whereabouts of a great treasure, and offers them a deal. If they help them make a clean escape, they could take all the treasure they wanted. They agree, and the five of them barely escape and make it onto a small island where they meet Luffy and his crew. Unfortunately they were pursued and Luffy and Amanda are captured and brought back to their boss, the head of the Bayan Pirates, who is also after the treasure. Now Luffy and the others must battle the Bayan pirates and find the treasure that Amanda's father had left for his children. Amanda, who has always resented adventure and treasure because her father was constantly gone in search for it, finally understands his feelings. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":46,"endDate":{"day":6,"month":4,"year":2003},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":1237,"idMal":1237,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":67,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2003,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/1237","startDate":{"day":6,"month":4,"year":2003},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: Un tesoro grande un sogno","วันพีซ ภาคพิเศษ 2 ออกสู่ทะเลกว้างใหญ่ ความฝันอันยิ่งใหญ่ของพ่อ","Vua Hải Tặc: Vươn ra đại dương! Giấc mơ to lớn của bố!"],"title":{"english":"One Piece Special: Open Upon the Great Sea! A Father's Huge, HUGE Dream!","native":"ONE PIECE: 大海原にひらけ! でっかいでっカイ父の夢","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Oounabara ni Hirake! Dekkai Dekkai Chichi no Yume!","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Oounabara ni Hirake! Dekkai Dekkai Chichi no Yume!"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n1238-HdBlNr5vwNau.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#5dc9f1","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx1238-Rf2wqBrCwgvO.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx1238-Rf2wqBrCwgvO.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx1238-Rf2wqBrCwgvO.jpg"},"description":"For many years, Ex-Marine Lieutenant Randolph and his troupe have put on a play aboard his ship. Having lost his family to pirates, Randolph wishes to put on plays that will give courage to those who have also lost their loved ones to pirates. Unfortunately, Randolph must retire soon, and he is now giving his last performance. Luffy and his crew come to see the play, and somehow manage to take part in it themselves. But from Randolph's past comes a vengeful subordinate with a diabolical plan who has finally become commander in order to capture Randolph. Luffy and his nakama now must prove to the people that not all pirates are scum, and protect Randolph's final farewell performance from the bitter commander. (aired after Episode 174)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":45,"endDate":{"day":14,"month":12,"year":2003},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":1238,"idMal":1238,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":69,"season":"WINTER","seasonYear":2003,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/1238","startDate":{"day":14,"month":12,"year":2003},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece TV Special 3","One Piece: L'ultima esibizione","守れ!最後の大舞台","One Piece: Mamore! Saigo no Daibutai","One Piece Special: Protect! The Last Great Stage","วันพีซ ภาคพิเศษ 3 ป้องกันการแสดงครั้งสุดท้ายอันยิ่งใหญ่ ","Vua Hải Tặc: Bảo vệ! Vở diễn lớn cuối cùng","ONE PIECE TVスペシャル3 守れ! 最後の大舞台"],"title":{"english":"One Piece Special: Protect! The Last Great Performance","native":"ONE PIECE 守れ! 最後の大舞台","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Mamore! Saigo no Oobutai","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Mamore! Saigo no Oobutai"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n2020-k3lHutyP9i06.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1bb35","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/2020.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/2020.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/2020.jpg"},"description":"Unlike the other specials, this story takes place in an alternate reality version of 19th century Japan, in \"The Grand Jipangu\", an alternate version of The Grand Line as opposed to simply being hour-long filler episodes.The story is divided into two halves: in the first, Buggy the Clown makes trouble in the town where Detective Luffy is stationed, and in the second a mysterious girl named Vivi appears. These stories feature cameos from several minor characters in the normal series. Surprisingly the \"Oyabun\" (Boss) specials did not stop there as five more specials were made following the first one, mostly as Christmas and New Years specials as well as fillers once in awhile.\u003cbr\u003e","duration":44,"endDate":{"day":18,"month":12,"year":2005},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":2020,"idMal":2020,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":68,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2005,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/2020","startDate":{"day":18,"month":12,"year":2005},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: Le avventure del detective Cappello di Paglia"],"title":{"english":"One Piece Special: The Detective Memoirs of Chief Straw Hat Luffy","native":"ONE PIECE 年末特別企画！麦わらのルフィ親分捕物帖","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Nenmatsu Tokubetsu Kikaku! Mugiwara no Luffy Oyabun Torimonochou","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Nenmatsu Tokubetsu Kikaku! Mugiwara no Luffy Oyabun Torimonochou"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/2386-jtduFM8raO2z.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#d6931a","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/2386-NQQkq1taHJ08.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/2386-NQQkq1taHJ08.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/2386-NQQkq1taHJ08.jpg"},"description":"Luffy and his crew take on the Villain All-Stars in a game of soccer in order to become the Dream Soccer King. The game comes down to a pk tie-breaker shoot-out with Coby as goalie and Helmeppo refereeing.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network) ","duration":5,"endDate":{"day":2,"month":3,"year":2002},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Comedy","Fantasy","Sports"],"id":2386,"idMal":2386,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":66,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2002,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/2386","startDate":{"day":2,"month":3,"year":2002},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: Dream Soccer King!"],"title":{"native":"ONE PIECE 夢のサッカー王!","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Yume no Soccer Ou!","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Yume no Soccer Ou!"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/2490-wlPYONPyTibY.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#ffbb43","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/2490-AL4WmnCJ5zvE.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/2490-AL4WmnCJ5zvE.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/2490-AL4WmnCJ5zvE.jpg"},"description":"Luffy and crew takes on Arlong's crew in baseball. Announced by Bon Clay and Buggy.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":5,"endDate":{"day":6,"month":3,"year":2004},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Comedy","Fantasy","Sports"],"id":2490,"idMal":2490,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":64,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2004,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/2490","startDate":{"day":6,"month":3,"year":2004},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: Take Aim! The Pirate Baseball King"],"title":{"native":"ONE PIECE めざせ! 海賊野球王","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Mezase! Kaizoku Yakyuu Ou","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Mezase! Kaizoku Yakyuu Ou"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n12001-IljdXqN8CTU7.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1e435","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx12001-XX0NNNfaKZ3e.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx12001-XX0NNNfaKZ3e.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx12001-XX0NNNfaKZ3e.jpg"},"description":"Toei Animation released a new 3D anime short at events starting December 1, 2011. The short run about 12 minutes long and played at stereoscopic 3D theaters at Aichi Prefecture's Lagunasia theme park, Nagasaki Prefecture's Huis Ten Bosch theme park, Kanagawa Prefecture's Yokohama Landmark Tower, and Hiroshima Prefecture's NTT CRED Hall.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":12,"endDate":{"day":1,"month":12,"year":2011},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy"],"id":12001,"idMal":12001,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":61,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2011,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/12001","startDate":{"day":1,"month":12,"year":2011},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"native":"ONE PIECE 3D 激走! トラップコースター","romaji":"ONE PIECE 3D: Gekisou! Trap Coaster","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE 3D: Gekisou! Trap Coaster"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/16239-pov53U1T1dRm.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1c900","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b16239-XzoVjd7JK8xJ.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b16239-XzoVjd7JK8xJ.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b16239-XzoVjd7JK8xJ.png"},"description":"The story of the Hand Island no Bouken special is set a little before the events of One Piece Film Z and depicts a major \"Hand Island\" incident during the New World storyline. The story is set at \"Cannon Town\" where a parent and a child work as craftspeople. The incident revolves around them and a commodore of a marine base. The special will also have a flashback scene to the story in the first chapter of the manga, but with new animation. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network) ","duration":102,"endDate":{"day":15,"month":12,"year":2012},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":16239,"idMal":16239,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":72,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2012,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/16239","startDate":{"day":15,"month":12,"year":2012},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"One Piece: Episode of Luffy - Hand Island Adventure","native":"ONE PIECE エピソードオブルフィ 〜ハンドアイランドの冒険〜","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Luffy - Hand Island no Bouken","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Luffy - Hand Island no Bouken"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n16468-yOxhsBHFICtu.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#feae28","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b16468-pMKFwfY8lYZX.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b16468-pMKFwfY8lYZX.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b16468-pMKFwfY8lYZX.png"},"description":"An exclusive anime prologue to One Piece Film Z with an original story penned by manga creator Eiichiro Oda. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network) ","duration":5,"endDate":{"day":30,"month":12,"year":2012},"episodes":2,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":16468,"idMal":16468,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":69,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2012,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/16468","startDate":{"day":23,"month":12,"year":2012},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: Glorious Island","One Piece Special: Glorious Island","ワンピース フィルム ゼット グロリアス アイランド"],"title":{"native":"ONE PIECE FILM Z『GLORIOUS ISLAND』","romaji":"ONE PIECE FILM: Z - GLORIOUS ISLAND","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE FILM: Z - GLORIOUS ISLAND"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/15323-zrax5OGlGepE.png","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#fed628","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/15323.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/15323.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/15323.jpg"},"description":"A retelling of the Arlong Park arc, with new animation.","duration":105,"endDate":{"day":25,"month":8,"year":2012},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy"],"id":15323,"idMal":15323,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":78,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2012,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/15323","startDate":{"day":25,"month":8,"year":2012},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Special"],"title":{"native":"ONE PIECE エピソードオブナミ 〜航海士の涙と仲間の絆〜","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Nami - Koukaishi no Namida to Nakama no Kizuna","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Nami - Koukaishi no Namida to Nakama no Kizuna"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SUMMARY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/19123-QyRShJCfnIWD.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4c95d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx19123-leET1CrSJknT.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx19123-leET1CrSJknT.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx19123-leET1CrSJknT.jpg"},"description":"The story arcs aboard the Straw Hat Crew's first ship Going Merry (Merry Go in some adaptations) are recreated with brand-new animation, from Luffy and Usopp's fight and Robin's disappearance to the crew's final farewell to the ship. Going Merry is treated as another member of the Straw Hats as Luffy, Zoro, Nami, and the rest of the crew set sail for the legendary treasure, the One Piece.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":106,"endDate":{"day":24,"month":8,"year":2013},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy"],"id":19123,"idMal":19123,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":78,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2013,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/19123","startDate":{"day":24,"month":8,"year":2013},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Special"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Episode of Merry - The Tale of One More Friend","native":"ONE PIECE エピソードオブメリー 〜もうひとりの仲間の物語〜","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Merry - Mou Hitori no Nakama no Monogatari","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Merry - Mou Hitori no Nakama no Monogatari"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SUMMARY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/20835-aR8CuXvtzqND.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e47850","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx20835-QVV6LpJlqe1A.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx20835-QVV6LpJlqe1A.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx20835-QVV6LpJlqe1A.jpg"},"description":"This new TV special tells the two years of Luffy's training with Silvers Rayleigh in Rusukaina Island after the Battle of Marineford, which has never been told in the manga or TV anime. It also features a new villain named Burndy World who is known as \"The Destroyer of the World\" and has the power of the MoaMoa Fruit (its ability is still unknown). Luffy has to protect Boa Hancock from the new enemy who escaped from the level 6 of Impel Down. He is newly designed by the original creator of the manga, Eiichiro Oda.\u003cbr\u003e\r\n\u003cbr\u003e\r\n(Source: Crunchyroll)","duration":107,"endDate":{"day":30,"month":8,"year":2014},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":20835,"idMal":25161,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":76,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2014,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/20835","startDate":{"day":30,"month":8,"year":2014},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Special 15th Anniversary"],"title":{"english":"One Piece 3D2Y: Overcome Ace’s Death! Luffy’s Vow to his Friends","native":"ONE PIECE “3D2Y” エースの死を越えて! ルフィ仲間との誓い","romaji":"ONE PIECE \"3D2Y\": Ace no shi wo Koete! Luffy Nakama to no Chikai","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE \"3D2Y\": Ace no shi wo Koete! Luffy Nakama to no Chikai"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/21230-5yju21iK6aMW.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1a150","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx21230-rfoUZud1Jn0L.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx21230-rfoUZud1Jn0L.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx21230-rfoUZud1Jn0L.png"},"description":"The anime will explore the childhood bond between Luffy, Ace and Sabo.","duration":110,"endDate":{"day":22,"month":8,"year":2015},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama"],"id":21230,"idMal":31289,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":74,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2015,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/21230","startDate":{"day":22,"month":8,"year":2015},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: Episode of Sabo - The Three Brothers' Bond: The Miraculous Reunion and the Inherited Will"],"title":{"english":"One Piece - Episode of Sabo: Bond of Three Brothers - A Miraculous Reunion and an Inherited Will","native":"ONE PIECE エピソードオブサボ ~3兄弟の絆 奇跡の再会と受け継がれる意志~","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Sabo - 3-Kyoudai no Kizuna Kiseki no Saikai to Uketsugareru Ishi","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Sabo - 3-Kyoudai no Kizuna Kiseki no Saikai to Uketsugareru Ishi"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SUMMARY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/21485-lPFbmxGrFsBX.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4bb43","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/21485-KR1sv4rYSe6V.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/21485-KR1sv4rYSe6V.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/21485-KR1sv4rYSe6V.jpg"},"description":"The Davy Back Fight Arc competitors journey to New World with new crew members Dojaku, Kansho and tactical genius Komei for a meeting that will take place on a foggy island that makes devil fruit users unable to use to their abilities.","duration":116,"endDate":{"day":19,"month":12,"year":2015},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy"],"id":21485,"idMal":32051,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":69,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2015,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/21485","startDate":{"day":19,"month":12,"year":2015},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece - Aventura en Nebulandia"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Adventure of Nebulandia","native":"ONE PIECE 〜アドベンチャー オブ ネブランディア〜","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Adventure of Nebulandia","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Adventure of Nebulandia"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/21831-Xl4r2uBaaKU4.png","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1a10d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx21831-qj5IKYiPOupF.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx21831-qj5IKYiPOupF.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx21831-qj5IKYiPOupF.jpg"},"description":"The Straw Hat Pirates meet Olga, a girl who has escaped the island Alchemi. Alchemi was known for its metal production, and for the creation of the extremely valuable Pure Gold, but the island disappeared two hundred years ago. Olga is now being pursued by Marines, interested in Pure Gold. Gildo Tesoro, who controls the Navy HQ and black market, hears of Olga and hires treasure hunter Mad Treasure to track her down. The Straw Hats join forces with Olga in search of the Pure Gold, while she plots to takes advantage of them and use the treasure to become rich herself.","duration":104,"endDate":{"day":16,"month":7,"year":2016},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy"],"id":21831,"idMal":33338,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":73,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2016,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/21831","startDate":{"day":16,"month":7,"year":2016},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"One Piece: Heart of Gold","native":"ONE PIECE 〜ハートオブゴールド〜","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Heart of Gold","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Heart of Gold"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/99302-v3NwmsSnjj94.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#bbe45d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx99302-b40WIhc5dylo.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx99302-b40WIhc5dylo.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx99302-b40WIhc5dylo.jpg"},"description":"The special will be a completely new work, featuring reanimated scenes from the beginning of the series through when the crew enters the Grand Line.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\nThe special is commemorating the manga's 20th anniversary, and will also feature anime versions of the original manga's chapter cover stories as part of the special's ending credits. The staff haven't yet clarified which cover story or stories will be animated. Additionally, the anime will feature a special 20th anniversary commemoration version of the original opening theme song \"We Are!\".\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":106,"endDate":{"day":26,"month":8,"year":2017},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Drama"],"id":99302,"idMal":36215,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":76,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2017,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/99302","startDate":{"day":26,"month":8,"year":2017},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"One Piece: Episode of East Blue","native":"ONE PIECE エピソードオブ東の海〜ルフィと4人の仲間の大冒険!!〜","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Episode of East Blue - Luffy to 4-nin no Nakama no Daibouken","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Episode of East Blue - Luffy to 4-nin no Nakama no Daibouken"},"trailer":{"id":"XcWmgU7X-Is","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/XcWmgU7X-Is/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SUMMARY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/459-JqlCjcwxxFrr.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e40d0d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx459-Ivw65mUXackh.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx459-Ivw65mUXackh.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx459-Ivw65mUXackh.png"},"description":"There once was a pirate known as the Great Gold Pirate Woonan, who obtained almost 1/3 of the world's gold. Over the course of a few years, the pirate's existence faded, and a legend grew that he disappeared with his gold to a remote island, an island pirates continue to search for. Aboard the Going Merry, Luffy and his crew, starved and reckless, are robbed of their treasure. In an attempt to get it back, they wreck the getaway ship, guided by a young boy named Tabio, who's a captured part of El Drago's pirate crew. El Drago's love for gold has driven him to look for Woonan's island, and thanks to Woonan's treasure map, he finds it. During this time, Luffy's crew have been split up, and despite their own circumstances, they must find a way to stop El Drago from obtaining Woonan's gold. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":50,"endDate":{"day":4,"month":3,"year":2000},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":459,"idMal":459,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":68,"season":"WINTER","seasonYear":2000,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/459","startDate":{"day":4,"month":3,"year":2000},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: The Movie","One Piece (2000)","One Piece: La Película","วันพีซ เดอะมูฟวี่ 1 เกาะสมบัติแห่งวูนัน","Vua Hải Tặc: Đảo Châu Báu","One Piece: Golden Island Adventure","One Piece - Per tutto l'oro del mondo"],"title":{"english":"ONE PIECE: The Movie","native":"ONE PIECE (Movie)","romaji":"ONE PIECE (Movie)","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE (Movie)"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/460-mWAlHAJ5MuBg.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4c943","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx460-p9HObfGUhWn0.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx460-p9HObfGUhWn0.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx460-p9HObfGUhWn0.jpg"},"description":"Informed by the Thief Brothers his ship has been stolen by the Trump Kyoudai (Trump Siblings) who have set up base on Clockwork Island. Monkey D. Luffy, Captain of the Going Merry and aspiring Pirate King works with his crew - Ussop, Zoro, Sanji and Nami to battle their way up Clockwork Island to reclaim their ship.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":55,"endDate":{"day":3,"month":3,"year":2001},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":460,"idMal":460,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":67,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2001,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/460","startDate":{"day":3,"month":3,"year":2001},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Movie 02","วันพีซ เดอะมูฟวี่ 2 การผจญภัยบนเกาะแห่งฟันเฟือง","Vua Hải Tặc: Cuộc phiêu lưu đến đảo máy đồng hồ ","One Piece - Avventura all'Isola Spirale"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Clockwork Island Adventure","native":"ONE PIECE ねじまき島の冒険","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Nejimaki-jima no Bouken","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Nejimaki-jima no Bouken"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/461-0pvcIaXC0p70.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e49343","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx461-DC9fMDl3AaK1.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx461-DC9fMDl3AaK1.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx461-DC9fMDl3AaK1.jpg"},"description":"The crew comes upon Crown Island where the animals can talk and they makes Chopper their new king. But there are human hunters there also looking for the legendary horns that will give the person who consumes it immense power. Luffy and friends must stop them from destroying this animal kingdom.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":55,"endDate":{"day":2,"month":3,"year":2002},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":461,"idMal":461,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":64,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2002,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/461","startDate":{"day":2,"month":3,"year":2002},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Movie 03","วันพีซ เดอะมูฟวี่ 3 เกาะแห่งสรรพสัตว์และราชันย์ช็อปเปอร์ ","Vua Hải Tặc: Vương quốc Chopper trên đảo của những sinh vật lạ","One Piece: Chopper Kingdom of Strange Animal Island","One Piece - Il tesoro del re"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Chopper’s Kingdom on the Island of Strange Animals","native":"ONE PIECE 珍獣島のチョッパー王国","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Chinjuu-jima no Chopper Oukoku","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Chinjuu-jima no Chopper Oukoku"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/462-Z074owEvilUu.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e49343","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx462-Ig8zfdsFWcql.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx462-Ig8zfdsFWcql.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx462-Ig8zfdsFWcql.png"},"description":"Luffy and crew arrive at the harbour of Anabaru. The local casino is holding a competition in which the winner will obtain a huge monetary reward if he reaches the finishing line first. Nami is elated and decides to participate in the competition. However, there is a conspiracy going behind the competition and the mastermind is an ex-military commander, Gasparde. His plan is to lure all the pirates to the military base and send them to their deaths. Luffy and gang have to overcome the numerous tests and tribulations along the way to complete this dead-end adventure. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":95,"endDate":{"day":1,"month":3,"year":2003},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":462,"idMal":462,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":72,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2003,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/462","startDate":{"day":1,"month":3,"year":2003},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Movie 04","One Piece: La Aventura sin Salida","The Adventure of Deadend","One Piece: Dead End","วันพีซ เดอะมูฟวี่ 4 การผจญภัยที่เดดเอนด์","Vua Hải Tặc: Cuộc đua tử thần","One Piece - Trappola mortale"],"title":{"english":"One Piece The Movie: The Dead End Adventure","native":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE デッドエンドの冒険","romaji":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE: Dead End no Bouken","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE: Dead End no Bouken"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/463-zgU5XjUCR7Kv.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e45078","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx463-QDnETPoHp9oD.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx463-QDnETPoHp9oD.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx463-QDnETPoHp9oD.jpg"},"description":"Luffy and crew go to an island searching for a legendary sword, said to be the most expensive in the world. Soon attacking marines and beautiful maidens split the crew. Zoro betrays the crew to help an old friend, Luffy and Usopp wander through a cave, and the rest help a village fight marines. When Zoro defeats Sanji he takes the sacred pearls that are the only defense against the evil sword that will plunge the world into darkness. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":95,"endDate":{"day":6,"month":3,"year":2004},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":463,"idMal":463,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":67,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2004,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/463","startDate":{"day":6,"month":3,"year":2004},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Movie 05","One Piece: La Maldición de la Espada Sagrada","One Piece: The Cursed Holy Sword","One Piece : La malédiction de l'épée sacrée","วันพีซ เดอะมูฟวี่ 5 วันดวลดาบ ต้องสาปมรณะ ","Vua Hải Tặc: Thánh kiếm bị nguyền rủa","One Piece - Der Fluch des heiligen Schwerts","One Piece - La spada delle sette stelle"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: The Curse of the Sacred Sword","native":"ONE PIECE 呪われた聖剣","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Norowareta Seiken","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Norowareta Seiken"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/464-wmQoE1Ywxghs.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4a15d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx464-g4wcZPjbhY5j.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx464-g4wcZPjbhY5j.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx464-g4wcZPjbhY5j.png"},"description":"The Straw Hat crew obtain an advertisement for a recreational island on the Grand Line run by the Baron Omatsuri. Luffy decides to take this opportunity to kick back and relax. Unfortunately, when they arrive at the island, they are asked to compete in contests through unity for access to relaxation. However, there seems to be a mysterious air on the island, as the Straw Hat Pirates begin to fight amongst themselves, while Robin, Chopper, and Luffy individually search for the secret behind Baron Omatsuri's island.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":91,"endDate":{"day":5,"month":3,"year":2005},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":464,"idMal":464,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":78,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2005,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/464","startDate":{"day":5,"month":3,"year":2005},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Movie 6","One Piece: El barón Omatsuri y la isla de los secretos","One Piece - L'isola segreta del barone Omatsuri"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Baron Omatsuri and the Secret Island","native":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE オマツリ男爵と秘密の島","romaji":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE: Omatsuri Danshaku to Himitsu no Shima","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE: Omatsuri Danshaku to Himitsu no Shima"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/465-dYMZ6SHNeOkL.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#43aeff","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx465-qSRr0MKYhS0I.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx465-qSRr0MKYhS0I.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx465-qSRr0MKYhS0I.jpg"},"description":"The crew salvages a treasure chest from a sinking wreck, but inside turns out to be an old lady hiding. To get the Straw Hat Pirates to take her home, she promises them the treasure of a golden crown on her island, Mecha Island. When they arrive, their ship is first attacked by the lord of the island. But later he decides to use the pirates to help him solve the riddle of the Golden Crown.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":94,"endDate":{"day":4,"month":3,"year":2006},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":465,"idMal":465,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":68,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2006,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/465","startDate":{"day":4,"month":3,"year":2006},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: Karakuri Shiro no Mecha Kyohei","One Piece Movie 07","One Piece: El gran soldado mecánico del castillo Karakuri","The Giant Mechanical Soldier of Karakuri Castle","One Piece: Schloss Karakuris Metall-Soldaten","One Piece - I misteri dell'isola meccanica"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Mega Mecha Soldier of Karakuri Castle","native":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE カラクリ城のメカ巨兵","romaji":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE: Karakuri-jou no Mecha Kyohei","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE: Karakuri-jou no Mecha Kyohei"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/2107-Je0JIEoxx1VF.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4a143","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx2107-H8bRuRRbhCIJ.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx2107-H8bRuRRbhCIJ.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx2107-H8bRuRRbhCIJ.jpg"},"description":"A retelling of the Alabasta arc. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nRevolution is brewing in the desert country of Alabasta, but the Straw Hats and Princess Vivi know the truth: it's all a plot cooked up by Crocodile. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Netflix)","duration":90,"endDate":{"day":3,"month":3,"year":2007},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Fantasy"],"id":2107,"idMal":2107,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":70,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2007,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/2107","startDate":{"day":3,"month":3,"year":2007},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Movie 8: Episode of Alabasta - The Desert Princess and the Pirates","One Piece Película 8: La saga del Arabasta - Los piratas y la princesa del desierto","One Piece Movie 08","One Piece - Un'amicizia oltre i confini del mare"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: The Desert Princess and the Pirates, Adventures in Alabasta","native":"ONE PIECE エピソードオブアラバスタ 砂漠の王女と海賊たち","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Alabasta - Sabaku no Oujo to Kaizoku-tachi","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Alabasta - Sabaku no Oujo to Kaizoku-tachi"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SUMMARY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/3848-LXsSQtSFu4e9.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4e450","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx3848-SCnYGTn34Llt.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx3848-SCnYGTn34Llt.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx3848-SCnYGTn34Llt.jpg"},"description":"The movie is a retelling of the Drum Island arc with new music and animation. Vivi has been removed from the plot while both Nico Robin and Franky, who joined the crew after the Drum Island arc, have been added. The movie also has the Straw Hat's new ship, the Thousand Sunny. It has been stated that Oda will be creating a new character for this movie, Wapol's older brother, Mushul, who also appears to be a Devil Fruit user. \u003cbr\u003e","duration":113,"endDate":{"day":1,"month":3,"year":2008},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":3848,"idMal":3848,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":71,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2008,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/3848","startDate":{"day":1,"month":3,"year":2008},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Miracle Sakura","One Piece: Episodio de Chopper + El milagro del cerezo en invierno","One Piece: Episode of Chopper Plus - Bloom in the Winter, Miracle Sakura","One Piece Movie 09","One Piece - Il miracolo dei ciliegi in fiore"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Episode Of Chopper +: The Miracle Winter Cherry Blossom","native":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE エピソードオブチョッパー+ 冬に咲く、奇跡の桜","romaji":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE: Episode of Chopper Plus - Fuyu ni Saku, Kiseki no Sakura","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE THE MOVIE: Episode of Chopper Plus - Fuyu ni Saku, Kiseki no Sakura"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SUMMARY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/4155-2PkLjTHddz2s.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4ae50","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx4155-P5TDf6t6qFwX.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx4155-P5TDf6t6qFwX.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx4155-P5TDf6t6qFwX.png"},"description":"The story begins somewhere between the Thriller Bark arc and the Sabaody Archipelago arc. The main villain's name is \"Golden Lion\" Shiki. 20 years ago he lost a battle against Monkey D. Garp and Sengoku and was imprisoned in Impel Down, but managed to escape. After that he starts to collect his crew and steals Nami to make her his navigator. Luffy tries to get to Shiki's hideout to free his friend. ","duration":113,"endDate":{"day":12,"month":12,"year":2009},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy"],"id":4155,"idMal":4155,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":78,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2009,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/4155","startDate":{"day":12,"month":12,"year":2009},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Film 10","ワンピース ストロング ワールド","One Piece: Strong World","One Piece - Avventura sulle isole volanti"],"title":{"english":"One Piece Film: Strong World","native":"ONE PIECE FILM STRONG WORLD","romaji":"ONE PIECE FILM: STRONG WORLD","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE FILM: STRONG WORLD"},"trailer":{"id":"3n58UPvcD7I","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3n58UPvcD7I/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/9999-T5jCX3o3cxeN.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#ffa100","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/9999.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/9999.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/9999.jpg"},"description":"The entire Straw Hat crew began to search for Luffy's important straw hat after he woke up finding it missing.","duration":30,"endDate":{"day":19,"month":3,"year":2011},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":9999,"idMal":9999,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":65,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2011,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/9999","startDate":{"day":19,"month":3,"year":2011},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece 3D: Straw Hat Chase","One Piece 3D - L'inseguimento di Cappello di Paglia"],"title":{"english":"One Piece 3D: Mugiwara Chase","native":"ONE PIECE 3D 麦わらチェイス","romaji":"ONE PIECE 3D: Mugiwara Chase","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE 3D: Mugiwara Chase"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/12859-XjlBW6o2YwUb.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1ae5d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx12859-uQFENDPzMWz6.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx12859-uQFENDPzMWz6.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx12859-uQFENDPzMWz6.jpg"},"description":"Said to be comparable to the Ancient Weapons of old, the Marines’ trump card, the “Dyna Stones,” have suddenly been stolen by a group of renegade vigilantes. The terrifyingly powerful man responsible, former Marine Admiral “Z”, now stands in the path of Luffy and his Straw Hat Pirates. Can the Straw Hats defeat “Z” and his crew, or will the New World meet its end at the hands of this mad man? \u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Funimation)","duration":107,"endDate":{"day":15,"month":12,"year":2012},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama"],"id":12859,"idMal":12859,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":79,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2012,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/12859","startDate":{"day":15,"month":12,"year":2012},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Film 12: Z","海贼王剧场版Z","One Piece Gold - Il film"],"title":{"english":"One Piece Film: Z","native":"ONE PIECE FILM Z","romaji":"ONE PIECE FILM: Z","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE FILM: Z"},"trailer":{"id":"1gGt1Mg_zSo","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/1gGt1Mg_zSo/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/21335-ps20iVSGUXbD.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1bb35","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx21335-XsXdE0AeOkkZ.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx21335-XsXdE0AeOkkZ.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx21335-XsXdE0AeOkkZ.jpg"},"description":"In One Piece Film Gold, The Straw Hats are at it again in an all-new high-flying adventure! A gripping tale unfolds in the spectacular city of Gran Tesoro, where Luffy and his crew are drawn by dreams of hitting the jackpot. With so much luck, Luffy's winning streak can't possibly end. But behind the gilded curtains lies a powerful king whose deep pockets and deeper ambitions spell disaster for all.\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: FUNimation)","duration":120,"endDate":{"day":23,"month":7,"year":2016},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy"],"id":21335,"idMal":31490,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":77,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2016,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/21335","startDate":{"day":23,"month":7,"year":2016},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Film 13","航海王之黄金城"],"title":{"english":"One Piece Film: Gold","native":"ONE PIECE FILM GOLD","romaji":"ONE PIECE FILM: GOLD","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE FILM: GOLD"},"trailer":{"id":"_shEgcWHC2U","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_shEgcWHC2U/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/n96427-UsjDRx1o4V8V.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4861a","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx96427-XiDc44cTlf29.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx96427-XiDc44cTlf29.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/small/bx96427-XiDc44cTlf29.png"},"description":"One Piece: Loguetown Arc is a novelization of Eiichiro Oda's intended story elements for the Loguetown Arc, later used in the anime as a filler (Episodes 50-51).\n","endDate":{},"format":"NOVEL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":96427,"idMal":94534,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":74,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/manga/96427","startDate":{"day":17,"month":7,"year":2000},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["ONE PIECE: Loguetown Arc","Logue Town"],"title":{"native":"ONE PIECE ローグタウン編","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Loguetown-hen","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Loguetown-hen"},"type":"MANGA"},"relationType":"SOURCE"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/30013-hbbRZqC5MjYh.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1935d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx30013-BeslEMqiPhlk.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx30013-BeslEMqiPhlk.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/small/bx30013-BeslEMqiPhlk.jpg"},"description":"As a child, Monkey D. Luffy was inspired to become a pirate by listening to the tales of the buccaneer \"Red-Haired\" Shanks. But his life changed when Luffy accidentally ate the Gum-Gum Devil Fruit and gained the power to stretch like rubber...at the cost of never being able to swim again! Years later, still vowing to become the king of the pirates, Luffy sets out on his adventure...one guy alone in a rowboat, in search of the legendary \"One Piece,\" said to be the greatest treasure in the world...\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: VIZ Media)","endDate":{},"format":"MANGA","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":30013,"idMal":13,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":91,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/manga/30013","startDate":{"day":22,"month":7,"year":1997},"status":"RELEASING","synonyms":["원피스","וואן פיס ","One Piece - Большой куш","ワンピース","ONE PIECE～航海王～","วันพีซ"],"title":{"english":"One Piece","native":"ONE PIECE","romaji":"ONE PIECE","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE"},"trailer":{"id":"z_qWsQNWSVI","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/z_qWsQNWSVI/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"MANGA"},"relationType":"SOURCE"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/101918-jUG4Mb1hCxVS.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#5dc9f1","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx101918-3uyCYHw1syki.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx101918-3uyCYHw1syki.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx101918-3uyCYHw1syki.png"},"description":"The special will be the first in the \"Episode of\" series to cover the Skypeia arc, and will feature a character who did not appear in the original Skypeia arc from the anime.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":105,"endDate":{"day":25,"month":8,"year":2018},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy"],"id":101918,"idMal":37902,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":70,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2018,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/101918","startDate":{"day":25,"month":8,"year":2018},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"One Piece: Episode of Skypiea","native":"ONE PIECE エピソードオブ空島","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Sorajima","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Sorajima"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SUMMARY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/8740-MlFelJndh6Yr.png","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e493a1","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b8740-oZajT3brPn7b.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b8740-oZajT3brPn7b.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b8740-oZajT3brPn7b.jpg"},"description":"Set over 20 years prior to the main One Piece story, this limited release OVA chronicles the confrontation between Gold Lion Shiki and Gold Roger as well as other events around the world around the time of the Pirate King's execution. ","duration":18,"endDate":{"day":16,"month":4,"year":2010},"episodes":1,"format":"OVA","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":8740,"idMal":8740,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":76,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2010,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/8740","startDate":{"day":16,"month":4,"year":2010},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"native":"ONE PIECE FILM STRONG WORLD EPISODE:0","romaji":"ONE PIECE FILM: STRONG WORLD - EPISODE:0","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE FILM: STRONG WORLD - EPISODE:0"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/105143-y8oSKa8PSsgK.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4e450","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx105143-5uBDmhvMr6At.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx105143-5uBDmhvMr6At.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx105143-5uBDmhvMr6At.png"},"description":"The 14th One Piece movie, which commemorates the anime's 20th anniversary, takes place during the Pirates Festival, an epic treasure hunt in which pirates from across the globe race to find an item that once belonged to Gol D. Roger himself!","duration":101,"endDate":{"day":9,"month":8,"year":2019},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy"],"id":105143,"idMal":38234,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":80,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2019,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/105143","startDate":{"day":9,"month":8,"year":2019},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["ワンピース スタンピード","One Piece: Estampida","航海王：狂热行动","One Piece Film 14"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Stampede","native":"ONE PIECE STAMPEDE","romaji":"ONE PIECE STAMPEDE","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE STAMPEDE"},"trailer":{"id":"S8_YwFLCh4U","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/S8_YwFLCh4U/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n102639-XXAO6eBYPBmw.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#d6ae78","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx102639-AjxqMLkusd2Y.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx102639-AjxqMLkusd2Y.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx102639-AjxqMLkusd2Y.jpg"},"description":"Brook introduces the Thousand Sunny's while Luffy searches for his straw hat.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\nThis was a special included in a limited edition DVD that was released in Nissan stores across Japan. The DVD also included the making of One Piece 3D: Straw Hat Chase.\n","duration":12,"endDate":{"day":5,"month":3,"year":2011},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":102639,"idMal":20871,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":56,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/102639","startDate":{"day":5,"month":3,"year":2011},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Nissan Serena x One Piece 3D: Mugiwara Chase - Sennyuu!! Sauzando Sanii-gou"],"title":{"native":"日産SERENA×ワンピース 潜入サウザンド・サニー号","romaji":"Nissan SERENA x One Piece: Sennyuu Sauzando Sanii-gou","userPreferred":"Nissan SERENA x One Piece: Sennyuu Sauzando Sanii-gou"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4c943","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b106492-ciLSI5nTJsV7.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b106492-ciLSI5nTJsV7.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b106492-ciLSI5nTJsV7.png"},"description":"\"Orb Panic Adventure!\" is a special crossover story featuring characters from One Piece, Dragon Ball and Astro Boy. It was created as part of many interactive crossovers screened at special events called Odaiba Boken-Oh to commemorate Fuji TV's 45th anniversary. It has yet to see a home release. In the following year it had a sequel called Kyutai Panic Adventure Returns!\u003cbr\u003e\n","duration":9,"endDate":{"year":2003},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action"],"id":106492,"idMal":23933,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":44,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/106492","startDate":{"year":2003},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Orb Panic Adventure!","Сфера панического приключения"],"title":{"native":"球体パニックアドベンチャー!","romaji":"Kyutai Panic Adventure!","userPreferred":"Kyutai Panic Adventure!"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n106572-kY1X9fF5zJZz.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4bb43","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/n106572-k1gqIsDcqGaV.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/n106572-k1gqIsDcqGaV.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/n106572-k1gqIsDcqGaV.jpg"},"description":"Prologue to the movie, showing the Whiskey Peak arc. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eReleased as part of a new cut for the movie's TV showing on \"Premium Saturday\".","duration":15,"endDate":{"day":20,"month":8,"year":2011},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":106572,"idMal":28683,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":69,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2011,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/106572","startDate":{"day":20,"month":8,"year":2011},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"native":"ONE PIECE エピソードオブアラバスタ 砂漠の王女と海賊たち","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Alabasta - Sabaku no Oujo to Kaizoku-tachi","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Episode of Alabasta - Sabaku no Oujo to Kaizoku-tachi"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SUMMARY"},{"node":{"countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1861a","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/n107110-pF0sMxDe3aLi.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/n107110-pF0sMxDe3aLi.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/n107110-pF0sMxDe3aLi.png"},"description":"Three five-minute stop-motion animated shorts by Banpresto that recreate the famous scenes from Eiichiro Oda's manga and anime One Piece.\u003cbr\u003e\nUnlike most figures, Banpresto's \"Cry heart\" figures are deliberately designed to encourage people to create their own stop-motion shorts.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":5,"endDate":{"day":22,"month":4,"year":2015},"episodes":3,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Drama","Fantasy"],"id":107110,"idMal":22661,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":59,"season":"WINTER","seasonYear":2014,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/107110","startDate":{"day":19,"month":1,"year":2014},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece: Banpresto's \"Cry Heart\" Short","Fuyujima ni Furu Sakura","Children's Dream","Ace no Saigo "],"title":{"native":"ワンピース Cry heart","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Cry heart","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Cry heart"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"OTHER"},{"node":{"countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1c9ae","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b107256-Pvgk6VnCmMZq.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b107256-Pvgk6VnCmMZq.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b107256-Pvgk6VnCmMZq.png"},"description":"A special that was part of many animated multi-screen Panic Adventure crossovers of Shueisha manga series that have been screened at special events called \"Odaiba Boken-Oh\" (お台場冒険王; lit. \"Odaiba Adventure King\") in Japan. These events were held from 2003 to 2008 to commemorate Fuji TV's 45th anniversary.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\nThe crossover was featured exclusively at the Fuji TV headquarters in the Kyutai (orb) section, where smaller screens partially surrounded the audience watching, each showing a point of view, while a bigger one would be used for close-ups.\u003cbr\u003e","duration":9,"endDate":{"year":2004},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action"],"id":107256,"idMal":23935,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":47,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/107256","startDate":{"year":2004},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Orb Panic Adventure Returns!","Сфера панического приключения: Возвращение"],"title":{"native":"球体パニックアドベンチャーリターンズ!!!","romaji":"Kyutai Panic Adventure Returns!!!","userPreferred":"Kyutai Panic Adventure Returns!!!"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n2385-kYxcxwV0LTvq.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#fef10d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx2385-06iBj9aNIadt.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx2385-06iBj9aNIadt.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx2385-06iBj9aNIadt.jpg"},"description":"Luffy and his crew are on Mirror Ball Island during a dance carnival. They are spotted by Marines just as Jango the hypnotist is running from them. Luffy and the others are caught up in the dance carnival as Jango, in his desperate attempt to escape, hypnotizes the entire island to dance the night away.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":6,"endDate":{"day":3,"month":3,"year":2001},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":2385,"idMal":2385,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":67,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2001,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/2385","startDate":{"day":3,"month":3,"year":2001},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"english":"One Piece: Django's Dance Carnival","native":"ONE PIECE ねじまき島の冒険 ジャンゴのダンスカーニバル","romaji":"ONE PIECE: Nejimaki-jima no Bouken - Jango no Dance Carnival","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: Nejimaki-jima no Bouken - Jango no Dance Carnival"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/101099-KarIxewMysiK.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#a1a135","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b101099-3AoCbJWTj2cV.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b101099-3AoCbJWTj2cV.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b101099-3AoCbJWTj2cV.jpg"},"description":"Series of commercials launched by Nissin Foods' Cup Noodles brand. Among some original content, the commercials also featured characters from prominent anime series including:\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n- Kiki's Delivery Service\u003cbr\u003e\n- Heidi: Girl of the Alps\u003cbr\u003e\n- Sazae-san\u003cbr\u003e\n- One Piece\n","duration":1,"endDate":{"day":7,"month":2,"year":2020},"episodes":11,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Romance","Slice of Life"],"id":101099,"idMal":35770,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":62,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/101099","startDate":{"day":7,"month":6,"year":2017},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Hungry Days: Yokoku-hen","Hungry Days: Majo no Takkyuubin-hen","Hungry Days: Heidi-hen","Hungry Days: Sazae-san-hen","Hungry Days: One Piece","Hungry Days: Zoro-hen","Hungry Days: Nami-hen","Hungry Days: Vivi-hen","Hungry Days: Choujou Gibasen-hen"],"title":{"native":"HUNGRY DAYS　アオハルかよ。","romaji":"HUNGRY DAYS: Aoharu ka yo.","userPreferred":"HUNGRY DAYS: Aoharu ka yo."},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/21880-9gGzVvnzqiNA.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e4a135","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx21880-uxsZ880LXSdY.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx21880-uxsZ880LXSdY.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx21880-uxsZ880LXSdY.jpg"},"description":"A short prequel to One Piece Film: Gold featuring the nine Straw hat crew members on the ship, planning what to do when they arrive the Casino.","duration":10,"endDate":{"day":2,"month":7,"year":2016},"episodes":1,"format":"SPECIAL","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":21880,"idMal":33606,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":70,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2016,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/21880","startDate":{"day":2,"month":7,"year":2016},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"native":"ONE PIECE FILM GOLD 〜episode 0〜 711ver.","romaji":"ONE PIECE FILM: GOLD - episode 0 711ver.","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE FILM: GOLD - episode 0 711ver."},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/5252-tlTORLa2dR2u.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#43a1e4","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/5252.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/5252.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/5252.jpg"},"description":"The Straw Hat Pirates, searching for the great passage \"Grand Line\", are in trouble when their food runs out! Luffy, searching for food on his own, finds a ship belonging to the pirate, Gary, and takes it over!! He lands at a nearby town...\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nLuffy was attacked by a young girl, Silk, who mistook him for a member of the other pirate gang. As the two eat a meal, they tell their stories. Meanwhile, Gary and his band are burning with anger at Luffy, demanding payment from the town's defenseless citizens...!!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Jumpland)","duration":33,"endDate":{"day":24,"month":11,"year":2008},"episodes":1,"format":"OVA","genres":["Action","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":5252,"idMal":5252,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":70,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2008,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/5252","startDate":{"day":24,"month":11,"year":2008},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["One Piece Prototype"],"title":{"english":"One Piece: Romance Dawn Story","native":"ONE PIECE ロマンス ドーン ストーリー","romaji":"ONE PIECE: ROMANCE DAWN STORY","userPreferred":"ONE PIECE: ROMANCE DAWN STORY"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"ALTERNATIVE"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/n30793-SDlOKsKEVHxa.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1ae5d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx30793-Zca4SIWG5j8e.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx30793-Zca4SIWG5j8e.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/small/bx30793-Zca4SIWG5j8e.png"},"description":"A collection of short stories drawn by Oda Eiichiro before One Piece became a major hit. \nIncludes:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nWanted! (1992) \u003cbr\u003e\nGod's Gift for the Future (1993) \u003cbr\u003e\nIkki Yakou (1993) \u003cbr\u003e\nMonsters (1994) \u003cbr\u003e\nRomance Dawn (Version 2, 1996) \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nTo celebrate the 20th anniversary of the One Piece TV anime, Romance Dawn version 2 was adapted into a TV special. (Episode 907)","endDate":{},"format":"MANGA","genres":["Action","Comedy"],"id":30793,"idMal":793,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":70,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/manga/30793","startDate":{"day":4,"month":11,"year":1998},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["원티드(WANTED!)"],"title":{"english":"Wanted! Eiichiro Oda Before One Piece ","native":"WANTED！ 尾田栄一郎短編集","romaji":"WANTED! Oda Eiichiro Tanpenshuu","userPreferred":"WANTED! Oda Eiichiro Tanpenshuu"},"trailer":{"id":"3uaMeEcwvvU","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/3uaMeEcwvvU/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"MANGA"},"relationType":"SOURCE"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/113308-jvwBxZ1dJcVx.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1865d","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx113308-u6wWW3d01DSt.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx113308-u6wWW3d01DSt.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx113308-u6wWW3d01DSt.jpg"},"description":"A collaboration between Nissin Cup Noodles HUNGRY DAYS campaign x rock group BUMP OF CHICKEN: a full-fledged music video directed by Kyotarou Hayashi for the song \u003ci\u003eKinen Satsuei\u003c/i\u003e by BUMP OF CHICKEN. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThe music video follows the series of One Piece-themed \"Hungry Days: Aoharu ka yo.\" commercials in a what-if world of Luffy's Straw Hat Pirates if they were living as high school students. The theme of the video is about graduation, where the Straw Hat Pirates recollect the days of encounters, farewells, and adolescence through photos taken in their pasts. ","duration":5,"endDate":{"day":2,"month":11,"year":2019},"episodes":1,"format":"MUSIC","genres":["Drama"],"id":113308,"idMal":52139,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":77,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/113308","startDate":{"day":2,"month":11,"year":2019},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["HUNGRY DAYS × BUMP OF CHICKEN 「記念撮影」MV","HUNGRY DAYS × BUMP OF CHICKEN - Kinen Satsuei","HUNGRY DAYS × BUMP OF CHICKEN - Commemorative Photo","One Piece x BUMP OF CHICKEN","Hungry Days: One Piece"],"title":{"native":"記念撮影","romaji":"Kinen Satsuei","userPreferred":"Kinen Satsuei"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/114761-cgU5ZD6nQ911.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#0dbbfe","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b114761-C2xOMuA44zKY.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b114761-C2xOMuA44zKY.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b114761-C2xOMuA44zKY.png"},"description":"Eiichiro Oda's One Piece manga is collaborating with the japanese boy band Arashi on a music video to be released on January 4. Jun Matsumoto from Arashi commented that the timing of the collaboration was chosen to coincide with both the One Piece anime and Arashi's 20th anniversaries.","duration":4,"endDate":{"day":4,"month":1,"year":2020},"episodes":1,"format":"MUSIC","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy"],"id":114761,"idMal":40970,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":58,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/114761","startDate":{"day":4,"month":1,"year":2020},"status":"FINISHED","title":{"native":"A-RA-SHI : Reborn","romaji":"A-RA-SHI : Reborn","userPreferred":"A-RA-SHI : Reborn"},"trailer":{"id":"woqtlIbFJGU","site":"youtube","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/woqtlIbFJGU/hqdefault.jpg"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/n10033-u9ROjiLizrd4.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#50aef1","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/nx10033-V7xnlgAVtaVR.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/nx10033-V7xnlgAVtaVR.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/nx10033-V7xnlgAVtaVR.jpg"},"description":"In the world where the taste and texture of food are very important there is Toriko, a hunter of precious foods regularly hired by restaurants and the rich. A man with inhuman skills to capture the ferocious, evasive and rare animals to complete his ultimate dinner course and then the chef Komatsu, his current accomplice: a weak timid person who was inspired by Toriko's greatness and accompanies him on all his journeys on his quest for the course of his life.","duration":24,"endDate":{"day":30,"month":3,"year":2014},"episodes":147,"format":"TV","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy"],"id":10033,"idMal":10033,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":69,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":2011,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/10033","startDate":{"day":3,"month":4,"year":2011},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Toriko (2011)","Toriko (TV)","Toriko x One Piece Collabo Special"],"title":{"native":"トリコ","romaji":"Toriko","userPreferred":"Toriko"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/813-03ZLvWJgR6Wd.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e49343","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx813-ZhnFNOeCU5dQ.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx813-ZhnFNOeCU5dQ.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx813-ZhnFNOeCU5dQ.png"},"description":"Goku is back with his new son, Gohan, but just when things are getting settled down, the adventures continue. Whether he is facing enemies such as Freeza, Cell, or Boo, Goku is proven to be an elite of his own and discovers his race, Saiyan. He meets many new people, gaining allies as well as enemies, as he still finds time to raise a family and be the happy-go-lucky Saiyan he is.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Anime News Network)","duration":24,"endDate":{"day":31,"month":1,"year":1996},"episodes":291,"format":"TV","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Fantasy","Supernatural"],"id":813,"idMal":813,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":80,"season":"SPRING","seasonYear":1989,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/813","startDate":{"day":26,"month":4,"year":1989},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["DBZ","Dragonball Z","דרגון בול זי","What's My Destiny Dragon Ball","ดราก้อนบอล Z","Bảy Viên Ngọc Rồng Z","Драконий жемчуг Зет"],"title":{"english":"Dragon Ball Z","native":"ドラゴンボールZ","romaji":"Dragon Ball Z","userPreferred":"Dragon Ball Z"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"CHARACTER"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/126649-pxeImm81vD6l.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#e48628","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b126649-sbuKTAghtsln.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/b126649-sbuKTAghtsln.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/b126649-sbuKTAghtsln.jpg"},"description":"A Tokyo One Piece Tower exclusive film. It's a tie-in to a real treasure hunting event in collaboration with Takarush Corp. for a limited time called Treasure Hunting: Tongari Shima no Daibouken. During this, you’ll decipher the mysteries of ancient documents found by Luffy, Usopp, and Chopper, and then set out to find the nest of the mysterious animal known as Tongari Ton!\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThe film itself begins at the end of your treasure hunting adventure at the Tokyo One Piece Tower, where the Straw Hat Crew are tricked into opening a chest in a cave thinking it's where the Tongari Island treasure is.\n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: Otakumode)","duration":10,"endDate":{"day":1,"month":11,"year":2016},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy"],"id":126649,"idMal":38419,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":63,"season":"FALL","seasonYear":2016,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/anime/126649","startDate":{"day":1,"month":11,"year":2016},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Treasure Hunting: Tongari Shima no Daibouke"],"title":{"english":"The Great Tongari Island Treasure Hunting Adventure","native":"東京ワンピースタワー トンガリ島の大秘宝","romaji":"Tokyo One Piece Tower: Tongari Shima no Dai Hihou","userPreferred":"Tokyo One Piece Tower: Tongari Shima no Dai Hihou"},"type":"ANIME"},"relationType":"SIDE_STORY"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/134184-My4zIFu5a4j1.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#fe9350","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx134184-25CEkbRJEzXB.png","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx134184-25CEkbRJEzXB.png","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/small/bx134184-25CEkbRJEzXB.png"},"description":"This is the second version of \"Romance Dawn\" containing 45 pages, and was originally published in the Weekly Shonen Jump of 1996 issue #41 on 23 September. It has since been reprinted, along with a page of author commentary, in the Eiichiro Oda early-works compilation Wanted! in 1998.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ci\u003eNote: It was adapted into episode 907 of the One Piece TV anime that aired on October 20, 2019.\u003c/i\u003e","endDate":{"day":23,"month":9,"year":1996},"format":"ONE_SHOT","genres":["Action","Comedy","Drama"],"id":134184,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":72,"siteUrl":"https://anilist.co/manga/134184","startDate":{"day":23,"month":9,"year":1996},"status":"FINISHED","synonyms":["Romance Dawn - Version 2"],"title":{"english":"Romance Dawn","native":"ロマンスドーン","romaji":"Romance Dawn","userPreferred":"Romance Dawn"},"type":"MANGA"},"relationType":"SOURCE"},{"node":{"bannerImage":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/141902-SvnRSXnN7DWC.jpg","countryOfOrigin":"JP","coverImage":{"color":"#f1c950","extraLarge":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx141902-fTyoTk8F8qOl.jpg","large":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/medium/bx141902-fTyoTk8F8qOl.jpg","medium":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/small/bx141902-fTyoTk8F8qOl.jpg"},"description":"\u003ci\u003eAn almighty voice. With fiery red locks.\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nThe story takes place on an island where Uta, the world’s favorite diva, performs for the first time in public. Uta’s singing voice, which she sings with while concealing her true identity, has been described as “otherworldly,” and while the venue is filled with the Straw Hats led by Luffy, pirates, navy, and fans from all over the world who have come to enjoy her voice, Uta’s voice is heard in a new light. The curtain rises on the story with the shocking revelation that she is “Shanks’ daughter!“ \n\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n(Source: ONE PIECE FILM RED Website)\n","duration":115,"endDate":{"day":6,"month":8,"year":2022},"episodes":1,"format":"MOVIE","genres":["Action","Adventure","Comedy","Drama","Fantasy","Music"],"id":141902,"idMal":50410,"isAdult":false,"meanScore":78,"season":"SUMMER","seasonYear":2022,